comic_0 = Comic.create!({"country" => us, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/volume/4050-112010/", "count_of_issues" => 23, "date_last_updated" => "2023-01-24 06:54:06 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Kimetsu no Yaiba is set in the Taisho era, Japan.</em></p><p><em>The life of Tanjiro Kamado, a kindhearted boy who sells coal for a living, changes one day after his family is murdered by a <a title=\"Demon\" href=\"https://kimetsu-no-yaiba.fandom.com/wiki/Demon\" rel=\"nofollow\">demon</a>.</em></p><p><em>In order to turn back his sister, the only one who survived but turned into a ferocious demon herself, the two go off on a journey to seek the demon who killed their family.</em></p><p><em>A tale of bloodstained swords!</em></p><p>English translation of the Japanese manga <a href=\"/kimetsu-no-yaiba/4050-90821/\" data-ref-id=\"4050-90821\">Kimetsu no Yaiba</a> (鬼滅の刃).</p>", "cv_id" => 112010, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6497309-01.jpg", "name" => "Demon Slayer: Kimetsu no Yaiba", "publisher" => "Viz", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba/4050-112010/", "start_year" => 2018})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-717948/", "cover_date" => "2019-09-04", "date_last_updated" => "2019-09-04 07:16:35 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>After dealing with several demonic enemies aboard the Infinity Train, Tanjiro, Zenitsu and Inosuke must face the demon spirit of the train itself! Even if they can stop the demon train, the minions of Muzan Kibutsuji are still out there and Tanjiro must continue to improve his strength and skills. Learning the secret of the Hikonami Kagura and Flame Breathing will give him a powerful new advantage.</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 62: Ending In A Dream</li><li>Chapter 63: Akaza</li><li>Chapter 64: The Strength of the Hashira</li><li>Chapter 65: Whose Victory?</li><li>Chapter 66: Scattering Into Dawn</li><li>Chapter 67: Looking For Something</li><li>Chapter 68: Wielder</li><li>Chapter 69: Move Forward—Even If Just A Little</li><li>Chapter 70: Kidnapper</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 717948, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7059844-08.jpg", "issue_number" => 8.0, "name" => "The Strength of the Hashira", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-8-the-strength-of-th/4000-717948/", "store_date" => "2019-09-04"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-726432/", "cover_date" => "2019-11-09", "date_last_updated" => "2019-11-09 23:52:24 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Tanjiro and his friends accompany the Hashira Tengen Uzui to an entertainment district where Tengen’s female ninja agents were gathering information on a demon before they suddenly disappeared. In order to investigate, Tanjiro and the others disguise themselves as women to sneak in! As they close in on their target, the demon reaches out for the courtesans of the district!</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 71: Operation: Entertainment District</li><li>Chapter 72: Search For My Wives</li><li>Chapter 73: The Chase</li><li>Chapter 74: Daki</li><li>Chapter 75: Various Feelings</li><li>Chapter 76: In Various Places</li><li>Chapter 77: Roar</li><li>Chapter 78: Wriggly</li><li>Chapter 79: Air Hole</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 726432, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7137950-09.jpg", "issue_number" => 9.0, "name" => "Operation: Entertainment District", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-9-operation-entertai/4000-726432/", "store_date" => "2019-11-06"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-732620/", "cover_date" => "2020-01-08", "date_last_updated" => "2020-01-08 01:08:37 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Despite some comic misunderstandings that almost blew their cover, Tanjiro, Inosuke and Zenitsu have smoked out Daki, a demon that has been devouring the residents of an entertainment district for years. The Hashira Tengen Uzui and his ninja companions engage Daki, but if they cannot handle her, what chance do Tanjiro and his friends have of taking on one of Kibutsuji’s Upper-Rank demons by themselves?</em></p><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li>Chapter 80: Value</li><li>Chapter 81: Layered Memories</li><li>Chapter 82: Human and Demon</li><li>Chapter 83: Transformation</li><li>Chapter 84: What Is Important</li><li>Chapter 85: Weeping</li><li>Chapter 86: Gyutaro</li><li>Chapter 87: Gathering</li><li>Chapter 88: How To Defeat Them</li><li>Bonus Chapter: Inosuke's Fairy Tale</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The digital edition (1/7/2020) for this volume was released before the print edition.</p>", "cv_id" => 732620, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7203054-10.jpg", "issue_number" => 10.0, "name" => "Human and Demon", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-10-human-and-demon/4000-732620/", "store_date" => "2020-01-08"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-738944/", "cover_date" => "2020-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2020-05-27 15:31:57 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The battle against the powerful sibling demons Gyutaro and Daki is not going well. Although finally able to fight alongside Tanjiro against the monsters, Zenitsu, Inosuke and even the Hashira Tengen Uzui may all be overwhelmed. Battling even one of Lord Muzan’s Twelve Kizuki is hard enough—can Tanjiro face two of them alone?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 89: A Close Fight</li><li>Chapter 90: Grateful</li><li>Chapter 91: A Change of Strategy</li><li>Chapter 92: Worm, Simpleton, Stupid Coward</li><li>Chapter 93: Never Give Up</li><li>Chapter 94: Do Something</li><li>Chapter 95: Final Moments</li><li>Chapter 96: No Matter How Many Lives, Part 1</li><li>Chapter 97: No Matter How Many Lives, Part 2</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 738944, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7262218-11.jpg", "issue_number" => 11.0, "name" => "A Close Fight", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-11-a-close-fight/4000-738944/", "store_date" => "2020-02-26"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-759205/", "cover_date" => "2020-05-06", "date_last_updated" => "2020-06-23 10:51:48 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>For the first time in over 100 years, the upper ranks of Muzan Kibutsuji’s Twelve Kizuki are not full. Angered, Muzan dispatches the survivors on another mission. Elsewhere, Tanjiro journeys to a village of swordsmiths and has to explain how his sword was so badly damaged to Haganezuka, the smith who made it. While Tanjiro waits for his sword to be repaired, enemies close in…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 98: The Upper Ranks Gather</li><li>Chapter 99: Someone's Dream</li><li>Chapter 100: Go To the Village!!</li><li>Chapter 101: A Secret</li><li>Chapter 102: Hello, Tokito</li><li>Chapter 103: Yoriichi Type Zero</li><li>Chapter 104: Kotetsu</li><li>Chapter 105: Something Came Out</li><li>Chapter 106: Enemy Attack</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The digital edition (5/5/2020) for this volume was released before the print edition.</p>", "cv_id" => 759205, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7363877-12.jpg", "issue_number" => 12.0, "name" => "The Upper Ranks Gather", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-12-the-upper-ranks-g/4000-759205/", "store_date" => "2020-06-24"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-766201/", "cover_date" => "2020-06-03", "date_last_updated" => "2020-07-02 01:11:39 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The strange shape-shifting demons Hatengu and Gyokko attack Tanjiro and his friends in the hidden village of swordsmiths. The Mist Hashira, Muichiro Tokito, engages the demons, but he’ll need some help from Tanjiro and another Demon Slayer, Genya. It’s bad enough that they have to fight two upper-rank demons, but can they handle a foe who can split itself into four separate bodies and regenerate almost instantly?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 107: In the Way</li><li>Chapter 108: Thank You, Tokito</li><li>Chapter 109: Won't Die</li><li>Chapter 110: Sneaking Around</li><li>Chapter 111: Pretentious Artist</li><li>Chapter 112: Transitions</li><li>Chapter 113: Bright Red Blade</li><li>Chapter 114: Wanted: Respect</li><li>Chapter 115: To Be A Hashira</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The digital edition (6/2/2020) for this volume was released before the print edition.</p>", "cv_id" => 766201, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7405090-13.jpg", "issue_number" => 13.0, "name" => "Transitions", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-13-transitions/4000-766201/", "store_date" => "2020-07-01"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-776394/", "cover_date" => "2020-07-11", "date_last_updated" => "2020-07-23 00:30:12 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Tanjiro's sword is still not ready. The swordsmith Haganezuka tries to concentrate on finishing while Tanjiro and his friends engage the two upper-rank demons, Hantengu and Gyokko, in a ferocious battle. Hantengu continues to create different forms to attack the Demon Slayers. Meanwhile, the Mist Hashira Tokito regains his memories of the past and confronts Gyokko, but what will these memories reveal?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 116: Awful Villain</li><li>Chapter 117: Swordsmith</li><li>Chapter 118: The Mu of Muichiro</li><li>Chapter 119: Coming Back</li><li>Chapter 120: Trading Insults</li><li>Chapter 121: Abnormal Situation</li><li>Chapter 122: A Passing Moment of Excitement</li><li>Chapter 123: Mitsuri Kanroji's Life Passes Before Her Eyes</li><li>Chapter 124: Get Your Act Together, Moron!</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The digital edition (7/8/2020) for this volume was released before the print edition.</p>", "cv_id" => 776394, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7459614-14.jpg", "issue_number" => 14.0, "name" => "The Mu Of Muichiro", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-14-the-mu-of-muichir/4000-776394/", "store_date" => "2020-07-22"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-786547/", "cover_date" => "2020-08-04", "date_last_updated" => "2020-08-04 19:48:28 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Tanjiro finally chases down the main body of the upper-rank demon Hantengu. However, dawn is approaching, and the rising sun is a threat to Nezuko. Tanjiro's concern for his sister is a distraction from the focus he needs to fight Hantengu, and if he hesitates it could be the last mistake he ever makes! Elsewhere, Tamayo ponders the nature of Nezuko's curse and how she could be so different from other demons.</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 125: Dawn Approaches</li><li>Chapter 126: Daybreak and First Light</li><li>Chapter 127: The Rumble of Victory</li><li>Chapter 128: A Request For Instruction</li><li>Chapter 129: To Become A Marked One</li><li>Chapter 130: A Place To Be</li><li>Chapter 131: Visitor</li><li>Chapter 132: Full-Strength Training</li><li>Chapter 133: Welcome</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 786547, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7501078-15.jpg", "issue_number" => 15.0, "name" => "Daybreak and First Light", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-15-daybreak-and-firs/4000-786547/", "store_date" => "2020-08-05"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-797004/", "cover_date" => "2020-09-02", "date_last_updated" => "2020-09-02 08:49:07 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Tanjiro goes to see the Stone Hashira, Himejima, who intends to prepare him for the battles to come. The training to become a Hashira—a high-ranking member of the Demon Slayer Corps—is intense and demanding, and earning Himejima’s approval seems impossible, but Tanjiro won’t give up! Meanwhile, the demon lord Muzan continues to search for the location of Nezuko and Ubuyashiki.</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 134: Repetitive Motion</li><li>Chapter 135: Himejima Hell</li><li>Chapter 136: Moving</li><li>Chapter 137: Undying</li><li>Chapter 138: A Sudden Turn</li><li>Chapter 139: Falling</li><li>Chapter 140: The Final Battle Begins</li><li>Chapter 141: Vengeance</li><li>Chapter 142: Shonobu Kocho the Insect Hashira</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 797004, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7548770-16.jpg", "issue_number" => 16.0, "name" => "Undying", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-16-undying/4000-797004/", "store_date" => "2020-09-02"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-805336/", "cover_date" => "2020-10-03", "date_last_updated" => "2020-10-03 08:58:41 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The Demon Slayer Corps plunges into Infinity Castle to confront Muzan. Shinobu engages in a fierce fight against Doma, the Upper Rank 2 demon. Poison doesn’t work on him, so she finds herself in an intense struggle. Will she be able to defeat the demon who killed her older sister?! Then another demon appears before Zenitsu and blocks his way…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 143: Wrath</li><li>Chapter 144: Successors</li><li>Chapter 145: Box of Happiness</li><li>Chapter 146: Pride</li><li>Chapter 147: Small Cogs</li><li>Chapter 148: Clashing</li><li>Chapter 149: Disgust</li><li>Chapter 150: Noticing</li><li>Chapter 151: The Sound of Bells On A Snowy Moonlit Night</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 805336, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7597806-17.jpg", "issue_number" => 17.0, "name" => "Successors", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-17-successors/4000-805336/", "store_date" => "2020-09-30"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-815128/", "cover_date" => "2020-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2020-11-01 09:26:08 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The battle between Tanjiro, Giyu and Akaza continues. To beat Akaza, Tanjiro must use an advanced technique his father taught him—the Transparent World—which will push him beyond his limitations. Elsewhere in the Infinity Castle, Shinobu, burning with hatred, confronts Doma, the demon who killed her family. Can she take on the powerful demon by herself?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 152: The Transparent World</li><li>Chapter 153: Pulled</li><li>Chapter 154: Assaulted By Memories</li><li>Chapter 155: Useless Komainu</li><li>Chapter 156: Thank You</li><li>Chapter 157: Returning Spirit</li><li>Chapter 158: Chaos</li><li>Chapter 159: Face</li><li>Chapter 160: Similar Features, Returning Memories</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 815128, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7646099-18.jpg", "issue_number" => 18.0, "name" => "Assaulted By Memories", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-18-assaulted-by-memo/4000-815128/", "store_date" => "2020-10-28"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-819969/", "cover_date" => "2020-12-02", "date_last_updated" => "2020-12-02 03:30:54 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The Demon Slayers fight hard to get their blades closer to Muzan’s neck! To avenge her family, Kanao must continue to battle Doma head-on while Iguro and Kanroji find themselves slashing through the shifting rooms of Infinity Castle. Elsewhere, Tokito, Sanemi and Genya come face-to-face with a villain who recognizes Tokito, but Tokito doesn’t know him. Who is this powerful adversary?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 161: Flapping Butterfly Wings</li><li>Chapter 162: Trio of Victory</li><li>Chapter 163: Overflowing Heart</li><li>Chapter 164: Just Overdid It A Little</li><li>Chapter 165: Stunned and Trembling</li><li>Chapter 166: True Feelings</li><li>Chapter 167: A Request</li><li>Chapter 168: never Disappear</li><li>Chapter 169: Rumbling</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 819969, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7694179-19.jpg", "issue_number" => 19.0, "name" => "Flapping Butterfly Wings", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-19-flapping-butterfl/4000-819969/", "store_date" => "2020-12-02"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-675811/", "cover_date" => "2018-07-03", "date_last_updated" => "2018-07-03 03:25:07 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Learning to destroy demons won’t be easy, and Tanjiro barely knows where to start. The surprise appearance of another boy named Giyu, who seems to know what’s going on, might provide some answers—but only if Tanjiro can stop Giyu from killing his sister first!</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 1: Cruelty</li><li>Chapter 2: The Stranger</li><li>Chapter 3: To Return By Dawn Without Fail</li><li>Chapter 4: Tanjiro's Journal, Part 1</li><li>Chapter 5: Tanjiro's Journal, Part 2</li><li>Chapter 6: A Mountain of Hands</li><li>Chapter 7: Spirits of the Deceased</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 675811, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6497309-01.jpg", "issue_number" => 1.0, "name" => "Cruelty", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-1-cruelty/4000-675811/", "store_date" => "2018-07-04"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-683649/", "cover_date" => "2018-09-04", "date_last_updated" => "2018-09-04 03:22:34 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>During final selection for the Demon Slayer Corps, Tanjiro faces a disfigured demon and uses the techniques taught by his master, Urokodaki! As Tanjiro begins to walk the path of the Demon Slayer, his search for the demon who murdered his family leads him to investigate the disappearances of young girls in a nearby town.</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 8: Big Brother</li><li>Chapter 9: Welcome Back</li><li>Chapter 10: Kidnapper's Bog</li><li>Chapter 11: Suggestion</li><li>Chapter 12: I Can't Tell You</li><li>Chapter 13: It Was You</li><li>Chapter 14: Kibusuji's Wrath / The Smell of Enchanting Blood</li><li>Chapter 15: The Doctor's Opinion</li><li>Chapter 16: Playing Temari</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 683649, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6594479-02.jpg", "issue_number" => 2.0, "name" => "It Was You", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-2-it-was-you/4000-683649/", "store_date" => "2018-09-05"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-691218/", "cover_date" => "2018-11-05", "date_last_updated" => "2018-11-05 22:05:05 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Tanjiro and Nezuko cross paths with two powerful demons who fight with magical weapons. Even help from Tamayo and Yushiro may not be enough to defeat these demons who claim to belong to the Twelve Kizuki that directly serve Kibutsuji, the demon responsible for all of Tanjiro’s woes! But if these demons can be defeated, what secrets can they reveal about Kibutsuji?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 17: Arrow Demon</li><li>Chapter 18: The Curse</li><li>Chapter 19: Together Forever</li><li>Chapter 20: Zenitsu Agatsuma</li><li>Chapter 21: Tsuzumi Mansion</li><li>Chapter 22: Rushing Boar</li><li>Chapter 23: The Boar Bares Its Fangs, Zenitsu Sleeps</li><li>Chapter 24: Former Member of the Twelve Kizuki</li><li>Chapter 25: Believe In Yourself</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 691218, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6675930-03.jpg", "issue_number" => 3.0, "name" => "Believe In Yourself", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-3-believe-in-yoursel/4000-691218/", "store_date" => "2018-11-07"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-696232/", "cover_date" => "2019-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2019-02-11 21:19:20 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>After a fierce battle with a demon inside a maddening house of ever-changing rooms, Tanjiro has a chance to find out about the fighter in the boar-head mask. Who is this passionate swordsman and what does he want? Later, a new mission has Tanjiro and his compatriots heading for Mt. Natagumo and a confrontation with a mysterious and horrifying threat…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 26: Barehanded Fight</li><li>Chapter 27: Inosuke Hashibira</li><li>Chapter 28: Urgent Summons</li><li>Chapter 29: Mount Natagumo</li><li>Chapter 30: Marionettes</li><li>Chapter 31: Letting Someone Else Go First</li><li>Chapter 32: Pungent Odor</li><li>Chapter 33: Suffering and Floundering As You Move Forward</li><li>Chapter 34: Robust Blade</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The digital edition (1/1/2019) for this volume was released before the print edition.</p>", "cv_id" => 696232, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6744697-04.jpg", "issue_number" => 4.0, "name" => "Robust Blade", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-4-robust-blade/4000-696232/", "store_date" => "2019-02-13"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-702287/", "cover_date" => "2019-03-05", "date_last_updated" => "2019-03-05 02:19:28 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>At Mt. Natagumo, Tanjiro, Zenitsu and Inosuke battle a terrible family of spider demons. Taking on such powerful enemies demands all the skill and luck Tanjiro has as he and his companions fight to rescue Nezuko from the spiders’ web. The battle is drawing in other Demon Slayers but not all of them will leave Mt. Natagumo alive—or in one piece!</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 35: Scattered</li><li>Chapter 36: This Is Bad!</li><li>Chapter 37: Broken Blade</li><li>Chapter 38: Real and Fake</li><li>Chapter 39: Life Passing Before One's Eyes</li><li>Chapter 40: Hinokami</li><li>Chapter 41: Shinobu Kocho</li><li>Chapter 42: Behind</li><li>Chapter 43: To Hell</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 702287, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6828031-05.jpg", "issue_number" => 5.0, "name" => "To Hell", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-5-to-hell/4000-702287/", "store_date" => "2019-03-06"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-707979/", "cover_date" => "2019-05-07", "date_last_updated" => "2019-05-07 15:39:16 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The members of the Demon Slayer Corps are sworn to destroy demons wherever they find them—but the condition of Tanjiro’s sister, Nezuko, is a problem. What will the Hashira—the leaders of the Demon Slayer Corps—do about Tanjiro protecting his own demonic sister? Meanwhile, Kibutsuji assembles his own minions and intensifies his search for Tanjiro…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 44: Against Corps Rules</li><li>Chapter 45: Trial By Hashira</li><li>Chapter 46: Master of the Mansion</li><li>Chapter 47: Hmph!</li><li>Chapter 48: Butterfly Mansion</li><li>Chapter 49: Rehabilitation Training, Part 1</li><li>Chapter 50: Rehabilitation Training, Part 2</li><li>Chapter 51: The Nichirin Sword Returns</li><li>Chapter 52: Cruel and Heartless</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 707979, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6921533-06.jpg", "issue_number" => 6.0, "name" => "The Demon Slayer Corps Gathers", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-6-the-demon-slayer-c/4000-707979/", "store_date" => "2019-05-08"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-712877/", "cover_date" => "2019-07-02", "date_last_updated" => "2019-07-02 12:16:32 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>While under the care of the Demon Slayer Corps leaders, Shinobu, Tanjiro, Zenitsu, Inosuke and Nezuko have recovered. They have even learned a new and powerful technique—Total Concentration! They’ll need this new power and all their skill on their next demon-hunting mission aboard the mysterious Infinity Train as it takes them into the dreams of demons!</em></p><h2>Contents</h2><ul><li>Chapter 53: You Are</li><li>Chapter 54: Good Evening, Rengoku</li><li>Chapter 55: Train of Infinite Dreams</li><li>Chapter 56: Wake Up</li><li>Chapter 57: Draw Your Blade</li><li>Chapter 58: Good Morning</li><li>Chapter 59: Insult</li><li>Chapter 60: Defending 200 People</li><li>Chapter 61: Trading Blows At Close Quarters</li><li>Bonus Manga</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 712877, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/6990191-07.jpg", "issue_number" => 7.0, "name" => "Trading Blows At Close Quarters", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-7-trading-blows-at-c/4000-712877/", "store_date" => "2019-07-03"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-827178/", "cover_date" => "2021-02-03", "date_last_updated" => "2021-02-03 21:01:02 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>Their initial confrontation with Kokushibo, the most powerful of Muzan’s demons, has left Tokito severely wounded and Genya cut in half—but still alive! Can his regenerative power heal even this fatal wound? The Hashira Himejima and Sanemi square off with Kokushibo and unleash all the skill they have against him. Himejima is blind, but if he can see into the Transparent World he might have a chance. Who will survive this whirlwind of flashing blades?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 170: The Immovable Hashira</li><li>Chapter 171: Transformation</li><li>Chapter 172: A Weakling's Potential</li><li>Chapter 173: The Path of Opening A Steadfast Heart</li><li>Chapter 174: Nightmare On the Night of A Red Moon</li><li>Chapter 175: Respect For Future Generations</li><li>Chapter 176: Samurai</li><li>Chapter 177: Younger Brother</li><li>Chapter 178: Even If You Reach Out Your Hand</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 827178, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7793246-20.jpg", "issue_number" => 20.0, "name" => "The Path of Opening A Steadfast Heart", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-20-the-path-of-openi/4000-827178/", "store_date" => "2021-02-03"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-841826/", "cover_date" => "2021-04-09", "date_last_updated" => "2021-04-09 01:36:52 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>The fight with Kokushibo, the highest-ranking demon among Muzan’s servants, is over. Although Himejima and Sanemi defeated Kokushibo and sent him to hell, the price the Demon Slayer Corps has paid is very high. Kiriya Ubuyashiki, the new leader of the Demon Slayers, struggles to recover from the losses. With the battle against Muzan far from over, the remaining fighters will need his help more than ever. Meanwhile, deep within Infinity Castle, Tanjiro and his friends come face-to-face with their nemesis at last…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 179: Feelings For Elder Brother, Feelings For Younger Brother</li><li>Chapter 180: Recovery</li><li>Chapter 181: Disaster</li><li>Chapter 182: Rage</li><li>Chapter 183: A Clash of Wills</li><li>Chapter 184: Leaving the Battlefront</li><li>Chapter 185: A World Without Scent</li><li>Chapter 186: Ancient Memories</li><li>Chapter 187: Innocent Person</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 841826, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/7902569-21.jpg", "issue_number" => 21.0, "name" => "Ancient Memories", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-21-ancient-memories/4000-841826/", "store_date" => "2021-04-07"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-856546/", "cover_date" => "2021-06-02", "date_last_updated" => "2021-06-02 22:46:51 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>After centuries of preparation and training, the Demon Slayer Corps has come face-to-face with their nemesis, Muzan Kibutsuji. It is a desperate battle and several Demon Slayers have already been killed. Tanjiro himself has engaged Muzan, and, despite giving it everything he has, is taken out of the fight! Although severely injured and near death, he sees a vision of his ancestor that may hold the key to finally destroying Muzan! Can Tanjiro recover enough strength to fight Muzan to the finish?</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 188: Sorrowful Love</li><li>Chapter 189: Reassuring Comrades</li><li>Chapter 190: One After Another</li><li>Chapter 191: Which One of Us Is the Demon?</li><li>Chapter 192: The Wheel of Fate</li><li>Chapter 193: A Difficult Door Begins To Open</li><li>Chapter 194: Burn Scars</li><li>Chapter 195: Bewilderment</li><li>Chapter 196: I Am</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 856546, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/8002592-22.jpg", "issue_number" => 22.0, "name" => "The Wheel of Fate", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-22-the-wheel-of-fate/4000-856546/", "store_date" => "2021-06-02"})
comic_0.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-876671/", "cover_date" => "2021-08-05", "date_last_updated" => "2021-08-05 23:17:55 UTC", "deck" => " ", "description" => "<p><em>In an epic confrontation, Tanjiro and his fellow Demon Slayers have fought on through the night, suffering terrible losses against the King of Demons, Muzan Kibutsuji. Dawn is breaking soon, and if they can keep Muzan at bay just a little longer, it will be the end of the centuries-long struggle. But Muzan, who will stop at nothing to destroy the Demon Slayers, unleashes his most terrible powers. If he can’t defeat the Demon Slayers, he may be able to cause them to destroy themselves from within. All fates and destinies will be decided as the sun begins to rise…</em></p><h2>Chapter Titles</h2><ul><li>Chapter 197: Tenacity</li><li>Chapter 198: The Next Thing We Knew...</li><li>Chapter 199: Millennial Dawn</li><li>Chapter 200: The Price of Victory</li><li>Chapter 201: The King of Demons</li><li>Chapter 202: Let's Go Home</li><li>Chapter 203: Voices of Encouragement</li><li>Chapter 204: A World Without Demons</li><li>Chapter 205: Life Shining Across the Years</li></ul>", "cv_id" => 876671, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/8084566-23.jpg", "issue_number" => 23.0, "name" => "Life Shining Across The Years", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/demon-slayer-kimetsu-no-yaiba-23-life-shining-acro/4000-876671/", "store_date" => "2021-08-04"})

