comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-118125/", "cover_date" => "2007-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-25 02:57:14 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Overview</em></p><p>Invincible and Rex Splode haven’t always seen eye-to-eye but when Dupli-Kate’s twin brother Multi-Paul comes to town, more than a little angry about his sister’s death, the two of them find a little common ground on which to relate – common ground called KICKING ASS!</p>", "cv_id" => 118125, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/787/236530-17993-118125-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 46.0, "name" => "Issue #46", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-46/4000-118125/", "store_date" => "2007-11-21"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-120920/", "cover_date" => "2007-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 15:35:06 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Tether Tyrant and Magmaniac RETURN! After months on the run form the police, these two villains have decided to make their return. U Invincible is in for the fight of his life, against these two formidable opponents.</p>", "cv_id" => 120920, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3664/271502-17993-120920-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 47.0, "name" => "Issue #47", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-47/4000-120920/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105347/", "cover_date" => "2003-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2021-03-21 12:06:10 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<h2>Synopsis</h2><p>Mark Grayson is a typical teenager, except the fact that his father is one of the greatest superheroes known to mankind. Mark is waiting to develop his own super powers - hopefully something incredible - so that he can follow in his father's footsteps, whether that means fighting inter-dimensional aliens or stopping a bank robbery.</p><p>While Mark is at work at the local burger mart he throws a trash bag so high into the sky that it disappears. And with that, it begins!</p><p>And what better way, Mark figures, to begin than to go out and fight some crime... in a yellow bandanna goggles and a track suit. While taking down the thieving villain Titan he is spotted by his dad. Dad's impressed, but not by the costume, and Marc is taken to the tailor Art to develop a costume. Ideally, Mark hopes, something iconic.</p><p>Later, Mark sticks up for a a kid at school who is being bullied, possibly forgetting about his own strength. The principle - who he's called in to see - creates his moniker accidentally by telling him he's not <i>Invincible</i>.</p><p>Soon Marc is taking on some more criminals, some diamond thieves, but now he's Invincible!</p>", "cv_id" => 105347, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185533-01.jpg", "issue_number" => 1.0, "name" => "Issue #1", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-1/4000-105347/", "store_date" => "2003-01-22"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105532/", "cover_date" => "2003-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2016-03-06 12:40:36 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>When Mark Grayson was a young child his father, Omni-Man, told him of his heritage: he was born on a planet called Viltrum, and chose to come to Earth as its protector. Since that day Mark has waited for his own super powers to develop, and when they do he takes up a costume and name - Invincible - and looks for his own way to be a hero.</p><p>While fighting an apparent game-console thief - a Mauler twin - Invincible is met by the Teen Team which includes a cute girl called Atom Eve. Atom Eve looks familiar, and she should: she goes to the same school as Mark!</p><p>Invincible and Atom, along with one more Team member - Robot - figure it'd be a good idea to see what the Mauler twin was up to. Why did he need so many game boxes? Seems that the Mauler twin<i>s</i> need the processing power to run their robot army. That's obviously not a good thing, and the trio figure they'd better stop them.</p>", "cv_id" => 105532, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185534-02.jpg", "issue_number" => 2.0, "name" => "Issue #2", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-2/4000-105532/", "store_date" => "2003-02-19"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105533/", "cover_date" => "2003-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2016-03-06 13:09:11 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>While the mysterious bombings continue (see <a data-ref-id=\"4000-105532\" href=\"/invincible-/4000-105532/\"><i>Invincible</i> #1</a>), it's just another day for <a data-ref-id=\"4005-5210\" href=\"/invincible/4005-5210/\">Mark</a> trying to work out what's normal while still being a superhero - an <i>invincible</i> superhero. First of all he quits his job, after all, what self-respecting superhero flips burgers in his spare time?</p><p><a data-ref-id=\"4005-40550\" href=\"/omni-man/4005-40550/\">Omni Man</a> - aka Mark's father - asks him whether he's interested in teaming up. \"Yes, that would be great!\" And so they're off, and it's pretty cool, and it's something Mark's always wondered about. Omni Man's pretty good. To be honest, he's <i>really</i> good. Just while they're flying he zips off to take care of a handful of disasters, and pretty much wipes out an alien invasion with only moderate help from Invincible.</p><p>Before heading home for the day, father and son take a look at something that's going on in Lakeside Mall: a bomb attached to a stranger. There's no time to save him; no time to decipher its source. The human bomb is thrown up and away. The mall is saved, but a green arm reaches around and grabs Omni Man away into another dimension. It's the one of the <a data-ref-id=\"4060-41165\" href=\"/flaxans/4060-41165/\">Flaxan</a>s they had been fighting earlier!</p><p>When Mark returns home - alone - he finally understands what it is his <a data-ref-id=\"4005-41160\" href=\"/deborah-grayson/4005-41160/\">mother</a> does: she keeps a home for her husband, believing with just the smallest glimmer of doubt that he'll come home, safe.</p>", "cv_id" => 105533, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185535-03.jpg", "issue_number" => 3.0, "name" => "Issue #3", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-3/4000-105533/", "store_date" => "2003-03-26"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105534/", "cover_date" => "2003-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-13 12:06:58 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><a data-ref-id=\"4005-5210\" href=\"/invincible/4005-5210/\">Invincible</a> heads over to the <a data-ref-id=\"4060-41090\" href=\"/teen-team/4060-41090/\">Teen Team</a> HQ to talk to <a data-ref-id=\"4005-40947\" href=\"/atom-eve/4005-40947/\">Atom Eve</a> above the recent spate of human bombs. She's away with <a data-ref-id=\"4005-41137\" href=\"/rex-splode/4005-41137/\">Rex-Splode</a>; her \"boyfriend\", as <a data-ref-id=\"4005-41166\" href=\"/robot/4005-41166/\">Robot</a> tells Invincible! That is one fact which Mark seems to be continually, and uncomfortably, reminded of: whether it be Rex and Atom kissing, or Mr Hiles mistaking the two for a couple.</p><p>While Mark and Sam are busy at school, Robot follows up on the human bomb case, discovering that the perpetrator is likely one of the teachers. In fact, there's only teacher with the known background and skills to pull off such a stunt: Mr Hiles. Invincible and Atom race off to their teacher's house. Hiles admits to his crime which was done to avenge his son's suicide by killing the types of people he holds responsible for that tragedy. To prove his point Hiles has turned himself into a human bomb too, leaving Invincible no choice but to get him as far away as possible as soon as possible (linking back to the opening scene of <i><a data-ref-id=\"4000-105347\" href=\"/invincible-/4000-105347/\">Invincible #1</a></i>).</p><p>At the end of the day, finally, Mark can go home for dinner. His dad, <a data-ref-id=\"4005-40550\" href=\"/omni-man/4005-40550/\">Omni-Man</a>, has returned from some alternate dimension. They're extraordinary, but somehow, still normal.</p>", "cv_id" => 105534, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185536-04.jpg", "issue_number" => 4.0, "name" => "Issue #4", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-4/4000-105534/", "store_date" => "2003-05-21"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105535/", "cover_date" => "2003-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-13 12:09:32 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Mark is doing his homework in his room when the phone rings - it's his father, Omni-Man. He needs help with a mission; a \"major baddie\" coming to Earth and it is Mark's job to keep him from coming into the atmosphere. That leaves one question for Mark, how is he going to be able to breathe in space? It shouldn't be a problem. Omni-Man can hold his breath for two weeks, so Invincible should be OK for a couple of hours.</p><p>Invincible heads into space but does can't see anyone at all. Then, out nowhere, Invincible is punched in the back. It's some alien Invincible has never met before. The two duel it out until Mark asks for a time out and a chat. Strangely, the alien allows it. Seems that the alien's name is Allen and that he's a member of the Coalition of Planets. Allen's job is to go around to assigned planets and make sure the superheroes assigned to protect them are doing their job. As they keep (telepathically) talking, Allen realises he's made a big mistake. He was supposed to go to Urath, not Earth!</p><p>Mark heads home to have dinner with his family. Warn-out and ready to go to bed he enters his room only to remember he never finished his homework. Oh well, back to his grind.</p>", "cv_id" => 105535, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185541-05.jpg", "issue_number" => 5.0, "name" => "Issue #5", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-5/4000-105535/", "store_date" => "2003-07-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105536/", "cover_date" => "2003-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2021-05-06 13:34:25 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Mark and his friend William go out for college orientation. While they're there, a Reaniman attacks the campus, forcing Invincible to stop it. The cyborg impales itself soon after challenged by Invincible, leaving Invincible non the wiser as to what it was after.</p><p>Later Omni-Man and Invincible are called out to Art: Looks like a power suit is missing. The prime suspect is Black Samson - the suit's potential owner and an ex-member of Guardians of the Globe. Samson's been a bit strange of late, ever since losing his powers he's been desperate to get the suit functional so that he can rejoin the Guardians.</p><p>Meanwhile it looks like the Teen Team will be breaking up: Robot's been offered a position with the Guaridans.</p>", "cv_id" => 105536, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185542-06.jpg", "issue_number" => 6.0, "name" => "Issue #6", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-6/4000-105536/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105537/", "cover_date" => "2003-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-14 04:49:50 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>The members of the Guardians of the Globe are all busy - well mostly, except for Aquarus - when they get the call to go to HQ. Some, like Darkwing, are busy ridding the streets of criminals, others are fighting super-villains, getting unwanted visitors from their past, or even trying to enjoy a picnic.</p><p>Once they've all arrived at base it's time to hear the emergency. Except, no one's admitting to being responsible for calling the meeting. And then they all start being killed by a force too quick to be seen. Finally, it's just The Immortal, and he sees who's responsible. \"You! I never liked you,\" he says. After killing him too, Omni-Man replies, \"The feeling was mutual.\"</p><p><b>Extended summary:</b></p><p>In Midnight City some thieves wait on a rooftop, about to rob the place. They converse about how the City has such easy pickings because of the fact that it has been cast into an eternal night and that it has been left mostly abandoned, it's only real threat being Darkwing. They are comforted with the belief that Darkwing can't be everywhere, that is, until he jumps down, taking them out in an instant. He then receives a Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert and leaves them tied up, letting his butler know to have them arrested and swiftly departs.</p><p>Kursk, a super villain, is blowing up cars in Moscow, while a woman is being mugged somewhere else while a girl tries to get a cat from a tree in yet another location. A red blur then passes all these places, stopping Kursk, the muggers and rescuing the cat. Elsewhere, a woman is at a park having a picnic with a superhero costume wearing man. In surprise she begins to berate him for doing his superhero work while she's talking and tells him that he should hope no one saw him in his Red Rush costume. He apologizes only to receive a Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert, apologizing again he leaves with her saying it's okay, she knows he's needed elsewhere.</p><p>In Boston a woman in bed wakes up to kiss her new girlfriend and says she'll be staying over more often. They are interrupted when a rock-man bursts in demanding that the woman come with him to speak with her mother. She then transforms into War Woman and fights him off by pounding him into mere rubble. She then receives a Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert and so apologizing to her lover for the damage she leaves.</p><p>On his throne in Atlantis, the fish-headed Aquarus sleeps, until awakened by a Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert. He heads for the base.</p><p>Deep in space, a Martian Man and a Green Man fight what appears to be a giant robotic worm. The Martian tells the green man to become intangible so that he can destroy the worm's circuits; the man does so and the two return to Earth. The green man apologizes to the Martian for not going intangible earlier on in their fight but is told their is no need for an apology. The Martian believed the green man was learning quite quickly. Before anything else can be said they both receive a Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert and fly to the base.</p><p>Up in the sky the villaious Bi-Plane tells The Immortal how he plans to irradiate the city of Denver. The seemingly indifferent Immortal hears him out and then proceeds to nonchalantly hurl him into space. The Immortal then receives the Guardians of the Globe Priority Alert and heads for the base, in Utah.</p><p>Arriving at the Guardians of the Globe base in Utah, the Immortal finds the rest of the team is already present. He questions them to see if they know why they have been called and learns that they too are completely in the dark and believed he had the answer.</p><p>Then in an instant they found themselves under attack and unable to resist and so soon all the Guardians, except for The Immortal had been brutally slaughtered.</p><p>The Immortal then looks around shouting for the killer to show himself. When he found the murderer he merely had enough time to say, \"YOU! I never liked you!\", before he is decapitated.</p><p>The killer is revealed to be Omni-Man who leaves, telling the headless corpse, \"the feeling was mutual.\"</p>", "cv_id" => 105537, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185544-07.jpg", "issue_number" => 7.0, "name" => "Issue #7", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-7/4000-105537/", "store_date" => "2003-12-31"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105538/", "cover_date" => "2004-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2021-05-06 13:34:26 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Funeral issue for the Guardians of the Globe. As most superhero get togethers go, this one also gets interrupted...by Sanford the Butler in powered armor!</p><p>Ryan Ottley begins art chores as of this issue.</p>", "cv_id" => 105538, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185546-08.jpg", "issue_number" => 8.0, "name" => "Issue #8", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-8/4000-105538/", "store_date" => "2004-02-04"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105539/", "cover_date" => "2004-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-14 08:07:11 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age. He's a senior at a normal American high School. He has a crappy part time job after school and on weekends. He likes girls quite a bit. but doesn't quite understand them. He enjoys hanging out with his friends, and sleeping late on Saturdays. at least until the good cartoons come on. The only difference between Mark and everyone else is that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet, and as of late, he seems to be inheriting his father's powers. Which sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? PERFECT STRANGERS PART ONE-Beginning of a brand new story arc, a perfect jumping-on point for new readers! Male bonding time! Mark teams up with former Teen Team member Rex Plode to thwart some evil, but how can the two effectively fight the bad guy when they really want to fight each other? Meanwhile events start to unfold that will lead up to the big issue 12 spectacular! If you've ever thought about picking up Invincible now is the time.</em></p><p>Tryouts for the new Guardians of the Globe. Also, the Mauler Twins resurrect The Immortal.</p>", "cv_id" => 105539, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185547-09.jpg", "issue_number" => 9.0, "name" => "Perfect Strangers, Part 1", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-9-perfect-strangers-part-1/4000-105539/", "store_date" => "2004-03-24"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-105540/", "cover_date" => "2004-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-15 13:22:18 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>The Immortal and Omni-Man throw down. Invincible shows up, things are not good.</p>", "cv_id" => 105540, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185580-10.jpg", "issue_number" => 10.0, "name" => "Perfect Strangers, Part 2", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-10-perfect-strangers-part-2/4000-105540/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-106421/", "cover_date" => "2006-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:37:12 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Martian armada is heading to earth, and Invincible is in Africa? Plus the return of Allen, and the Lizard League. </p><p>Allen the alien, wakes up inside a machine in the Talescria medical center. He says he can move now, and accidentally breaks the machine. A nurse robot,rushes in and tells him that he is looking well. Thaedus, leader of the Coalition of the Planets walks in and welcomes him back. He asks to speak in private, and reveals himself to be a Viltrumite. He tells him that he once stood against the empire, but he was the only one. He says to go get Invincible, for he is the key to defeating the Viltrumite empire.</p><p>Meanwhile at the Pentagon, Rick Sheridan is feeling inhuman, after his dramatic reconstruction. Donald reveals himself to be a cyborg and tells Rick his story so he can stop feeling so bad about himself. He offers his assistance, if he ever wants to talk, and Rick says ok.</p><p>At Amber's university her and her friends discuss Gary, the guy who Amber recently met. She says that she doesn't actually like him, and that she has a boyfriend. Her friends say that they have never seen or met him. Just then Mark opens the door, and invites all of them to go bowling.</p><p>Meanwhile in the Lizard League headquarters, a new person named Supreme Lizard declares himself the new leader of the Lizard League. He is immediately shot in the head, and King Lizard steps up with a smoking gun,  asking if anyone else wants to try to be leader.</p><p>At the home of Deborah Grayson, Oliver is doing great in his studies. His tutor says that at this rate, he will be teaching them in a year. Deborah is extremely pleased.</p><p>In space, a Martian Armada approaches Earth commanded by the Sequid controlled Rus Livingston. He tells his Martian slaves that he will not tolerate any distractions, for nothing will keep him from Earth!</p><p>Back at Amber's university they thank Mark for the great time. He complains to Amber about no alone time, and they say goodnight. He sighs and walks away.</p><p>At the headquarters of the Guardians of the Globe, Rex congratulates Dupli-Kate on her marriage. She says that maybe if he was more compassionate they would still be together. Shapesmith walks into the room only to be told, that a Martian armada is approaching, he is very worried considering he is secretly a Martian himself.</p><p>Invincible meets Atom Eve in Africa, to tell her that everything went ok and that he saved his Mom. They hug, and have an awkward silence, then kiss!</p><p>Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 106421, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/308/90782-17993-106421-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 38.0, "name" => "Issue #38", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-38/4000-106421/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-106647/", "cover_date" => "2007-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:48:24 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>With aliens from Mars on their way to attack Earth, Shapesmith reveals that he himself is a Martian and that the attack is all his fault. Invincible and Atom Eve team up with the Guardians of the Globe to face the Martians in space before they can reach Earth and take over. While the bulk of the Earth's strongest heroes are off-world, the Lizard League chooses that moment to strike. They attack an American missile base and threaten to destroy a populated Earth city with a nuke, an act which could start World War 3. The only people left to defend the Earth are Rex-Splode, Dupli-Kate and Shrink Ray.</p>", "cv_id" => 106647, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/308/93470-17993-106647-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 39.0, "name" => "Issue #39", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-39/4000-106647/", "store_date" => "2007-02-14"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-109270/", "cover_date" => "2007-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 15:19:25 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>With their ship destroyed, nothing protects the Guardians of the Globe from the harsh environment of space but Atom Eve's energy barrier. She tries to hold on to it but every second it's up saps her strength. Invincible tells the other fliers to push them closer to the Martian ship so they can get inside and they manage to make it just as Atom Eve's field drops. Once inside the team is met by angry Martians. Seeing Shapesmith, the cause for the release of the Sequids and the imprisonment of the Martians, they almost attack. The Immortal convinces them that teaming up against the enemy would be better than taking out their fury on Shapesmith. After Bulletproof kills a wandering Sequid the rest of them find the heroes and attack. The heroes fight back but they are vastly outnumbered. </p><p>On Earth the Lizard League tries to take over a nuclear base. They succeed and get inside, but Shrinking Ray gets in too. Shrinking Ray opens the door from the inside and lets Rex-Splode and Dupli-Kate in to face the League.</p><p>Back in space even more Sequids are attacking. Things look hopeless until Robot sets off a device that drives all the aliens back and knocks them out for long enough for Atom Eve to put up a protective dome.</p><p>In a mall on Earth, Amber Bennet, Invincible's girlfriend, gets closer to another guy.</p><p>In the nuclear base, the Lizard League lays waste to the heroes. Shrinking Ray gets eaten by Komodo, who also kills every copy of Dupli-kate, meaning her death as well. Rex kills the other members of the Lizard League, leaving just him and Komodo left to fight each other. Rex charges up another ball but before he can throw it Komodo bites his hand off. As Rex falls and screams in pain, the ball (in the hand Komodo bit off) explodes, killing the villain. As Rex gets up the cowardly leader of the Lizard League sneaks up behind him and puts a gun to his head.</p><p>Meanwhile, the Sequids begin to overpower Atom Eve's forcefield. Inside of it Robot tries to use his armor to create a larger version of the device he used earlier. Being outside the armor leaves him exposed to the Sequids, so when the dome eventually breaks and the aliens come rushing in, things look dire.</p>", "cv_id" => 109270, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/308/119041-17993-109270-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 40.0, "name" => "Issue #40", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-40/4000-109270/", "store_date" => "2007-04-09"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-109271/", "cover_date" => "2007-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:47:55 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>The story picks up right where the last issue left off. Atom Eve just passed out and her force field fell, giving the Sequids and opening to attack the Guardians. Unfortunately, Robot isn't done building his device so the team tries their hardest to protect him while he finishes. While the others defend Robot, The Immortal flies to directly attack the Sequid host but gets batted away. Shapesmith forms a ball around Robot to protect him as he works and the others take on the Sequid army. When Robot finally finishes building he gives the device to Shapesmith so he can pass it on to someone who can get close enough to the Sequid host for it to work. Thinking he can do it himself, The Immortal grabs the machine and heads towards the host but is smacked down by Invincible. Invincible forcefully informs The Immortal that he, Invincible, is stronger and faster and that the task is too important to let The Immortal's ego get in the way. Invincible is as good as he says he is and successfully activates the device in the hosts face. The Sequid parasites are all knocked out and Invincible is able to save the astronaut they had been using for a host. With the aliens momentarily stunned and the astronaut in hand, the Guardians of the Globe make a break for it.</p><p>In a nuclear base on Earth, a one-armed and battle-weary Rex-Splode kneels before the leader of the Lizard League. The villains pulls the trigger of the gun at Rex's head but somehow it doesn't kill him. Rex acts while he's still able and puts the bad guy down in a couple punches. Before he can celebrate though, he falls to the ground.</p><p>In the blackness of space far above all this, the Guardians of the Globe make it to the command center of the ship where the Martians are waiting. They thank and congratulate the team but demand that they leave the astronaut behind to be executed. The Guardians refuse and are forced to flee in a stolen Martian ship. Unfortunately for the Guardians, they are unable to use the weapons on the ship, which becomes a problem when other Martian ships get launched from the mother ship and start to attack. Since they can't attack, Invincible leaves the ship and takes on the others on his own. When he returns to his ship he gets nothing but praise from his teammates. Then he and Atom Eve talk about a kiss they recently shared. </p><p>Back on Earth, Mark visits Amber and finds her with another guy. She hasn't cheated on him while he's been gone but she likes the guy he sees her with. Mark learns this from peeking into the window and makes a decision. He flies around the building and walks up to Amber's room just as the guy leaves. He talks to Amber and after a long, one-sided conversation, Mark and Amber break up. The decision is mutual, Amber was going to say the same things Mark had if he hadn't said them first. She will pursue the guy she met in his absence and Mark will go after Atom Eve.</p><p>Mark goes to see Rex-Splode, the last surviving member of the team that went to stop the Lizard League. Rex complains about Invincible getting a parade while his mission had to be hidden, but afterwards he said he wasn't seriously mad.</p><p>At his home that night, Rus Livingston, the rescued astronaut, coughs up some Sequids and they crawl over his face and body. As soon as they fully control his body they say (to no one in particular) that it's only a matter of time before they take over the Earth.</p>", "cv_id" => 109271, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/308/119109-17993-109271-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 41.0, "name" => "Issue #41", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-41/4000-109271/", "store_date" => "2007-05-09"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-112028/", "cover_date" => "2007-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 15:25:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Month’s ago, despite Invincible’s defiance against them, the Viltrumites designated him the Viltrum agent on Earth, responsible for preparing it for takeover in 400 years. Now they have come to check in on him—and they’ve sent their fiercest, most deadly agent.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 112028, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/1867/159669-17993-112028-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 44.0, "name" => "Issue #44", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-44/4000-112028/", "store_date" => "2007-07-25"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125073/", "cover_date" => "2008-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2022-02-23 16:40:47 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Doc Seismic escapes form Jail, and captures all of earth's superheroes including Wolf-Man, Savage Dragon, and even the entire Capes corporation have been captured, and taken underground. During this time Invincible is in Africa trying to talk to Atom Eve about their little incident a few days back when Cecil pages Mark. He tells Mark whats happening and Eve, and Invincible go to help out. When they reach the underground layer Atom Eve, and Invincible are bombarded with monsters. Eve is caught off guard and knocked out. Wolf Man tries to help out yet is knocked out as well. Invincible fights off the monsters one after the other when he reaches Doc Seismic he is so exhausted that he falls to the floor. Doc Seismic yells out,\"I WIN!\"</em></p>", "cv_id" => 125073, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/11155/111554991/8385823-invincible048-000.jpg", "issue_number" => 48.0, "name" => "Issue #48", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-48/4000-125073/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125132/", "cover_date" => "2005-04-30", "date_last_updated" => "2018-04-24 21:29:24 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>What are Mark Grayson's powers? What is his origin? Who is he? Where did he come from? This BARGAIN-PRICED zero issue answers all those questions and more. An excellent jumping-on point for new readers, this primer issue brings new readers up to speed while laying down the groundwork for upcoming storylines. It's a MUST-HAVE for current and future readers of INVINCIBLE.</em></p><p>In issue 22, Mark Reveals to Amber that he is Invincible and not cheating on her or a drug dealer. In issue 0; Mark elaborates on his secret life. He explains his origin from start to finish--when he received his powers to when he fought his dad (Omni-Man). Telling Amer the story is still very difficult for Mark but it ends up bring him and Amber closer; which becomes very obvious in the end of the issue.</p><p>Note: this issue takes place between Invincible issues 22 and 23.</p>", "cv_id" => 125132, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185532-00.jpg", "issue_number" => 0.0, "name" => "Issue #0", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-0/4000-125132/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125141/", "cover_date" => "2006-09-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-10-02 19:35:14 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Oliver, Invincible's step brother, receives a new tutor. Robot introduces his new body (cloned from Rex Splode) to the Guardians of the Globe. Invincible visits Art, and discusses his girl problems between Atom Eve and Amber. During this time Amber gets a number from a guy named Gary who attends her school. Invincible changes the subject to talk about his father, and about the peculiar words he told him after he was taken away by Viltrumites, \"read my books!\". Art gives Invincible copies of his books and Mark is shocked all of these books are about space adventures, and the things that can hurt Viltrumites. Mark comes to a startling conclusion that through these books his dad is telling him how to beat the Viltrumites.</p><p>Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 125141, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185656-35.jpg", "issue_number" => 35.0, "name" => "Issue #35", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-35/4000-125141/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125143/", "cover_date" => "2004-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2021-05-06 13:35:48 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age, except for the fact that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? \"Perfect Strangers,\" Part Three, The status quo becomes a thing of the past when Mark's world is torn apart before his eyes. How will he pick up the pieces? Events in this issue lead into our big issue 12 spectacular! Don't miss it!</em></p><p>Omni Man tells Mark the true story of Viltrum, and how they are an evil race who help the people who decide to be ruled by their empire and kill the people who don't. He explains that he was only on earth to someday enslave it, and although he had made friends and found love, and for a time he was happy he knew it would have to change. He even admits that he didn't love Deborah Grayson. Mark tries to deny the whole thing, and tells him that he doesn't give a damn about Viltrum, and he will not enslave his friends and family. Omni Man tries to calm him down, and tell him that he does not know what he is saying. Mark tells him he knows what he's saying and they begin to fight!</p>", "cv_id" => 125143, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185581-11.jpg", "issue_number" => 11.0, "name" => "Perfect Strangers, Part 3", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-11-perfect-strangers-part-3/4000-125143/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125148/", "cover_date" => "2004-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2021-05-06 13:35:56 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? \"Perfect Strangers,\" Conclusion, Mark's world comes crashing down around him. After the events of last issue, Mark is left wondering how he'll survive. You have front row seats as Mark comes face to face with the most deadly foe of his short- lived superhero career. It's all been leading up to this, and you do not want to miss this issue!</em></p><p>Omni-Man attempts to convince his son to join him in conquering the Earth as the two do battle. He asserts that humans are too short-lived and fragile to really be treated as equals, and seeks to demonstrate this by remorselessly killing thousands indirectly as he fights with Mark.</p><p>Invincible refuses to accept his father's point of view, and continues to fight on despite being completely outclassed. Frustrated and enraged by his son's defiance, Omni-Man beats him near to the point of death, and asks what he thinks he would still have on Earth in five-hundred years time if he remained there. Invincible reponds that he would still have his father, and Omni-Man leaves the planet with tears in his eyes.</p>", "cv_id" => 125148, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185583-12.jpg", "issue_number" => 12.0, "name" => "Perfect Strangers, Part 4", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-12-perfect-strangers-part-4/4000-125148/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125951/", "cover_date" => "2004-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-15 13:40:53 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? Machine Head was the king of the super-villain underworld for years. Nothing could stop him: He was untouchable. Now, with the help of villain-turned-hero Titan, Invincible is almost single-handedly taking down the most powerful crime boss the world has ever seen, but he's got to get through a legion of super-powered cronies first.</em></p><p>Invincible helps Titan take down his crime boss, Machine Head. Invincible gets hurt pretty bad by Machine Head's henchmen, but the Guardians of the Globe show up to save him. In the end...it looks like Titan has taken over Machine Head's place.</p>", "cv_id" => 125951, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185618-19.jpg", "issue_number" => 19.0, "name" => "Issue #19", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-19/4000-125951/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125183/", "cover_date" => "2004-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-14 08:05:49 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? \"Perfect Strangers,\" Epilogue?There is nothing below him. There is nothing above him. For as far as Mark can see, there is nothing all around him. What happened to Mark last issue to put him in this place? What is this place? And what does it have to do with his future as a superhero?</em></p><p>Invincible is picked up by the government and taken to the Pentagon. In the meantime the whole world is watching the fight between Invincible and Omni Man, on tv...including Deborah Grayson. Invincible wakes up after being unconscious for two weeks, and Cecil introduces himself, as a man who knew his father very well ..or at least he thought he did. Atom Eve, and William both establish that they know Mark's secret identity. Cecil makes sure the world thinks that Nolan Grayson died in a horrible car crash...although Mark, and Deborah will always know the truth. Robot is demoted as the leader of the Guardians of the Globe because of the way they have been working together, and the near defeats. Cecil tells Mark that they have the whole conversation between him and his father recorded, and takes him to a secret room. That is where he tells him that the government needs a replacement for Omni-Man and Invincible agrees to the job. In the meantime William and Eve begin to get very close. Invincible receives a message from Cecil about trouble in space, and he meats Allen the alien who warns him about a Viltrumite living among the earthlings. Invincible explains that it was his father, and what happened recently. So Allen asks what he is going to do now? Invincible replies,\"Finish high school I guess\"...</p>", "cv_id" => 125183, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185586-13.jpg", "issue_number" => 13.0, "name" => "Perfect Strangers (Epilogue)", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-13-perfect-strangers-epilogue/4000-125183/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125184/", "cover_date" => "2004-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-15 05:03:59 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? They're back! The dreaded alien invaders from another dimension have returned seeking revenge! Invincible and Atom Eve are the front line against an all-out invasion of EPIC proportions. The end of the world is at hand, and our best defense is a couple of 18-year old superheroes. Let's hope they've got their hormones in check!</em></p><p>This issue begins with Invincible,and the Guardian of the Globe fighting the alien race of the Flaxans. Somehow they are not aging until one of their wristbands falls off and Invincible discovers their weakness. Invincible returns home to find the Immortal waiting outside his window, telling him that he doesn't trust him. When he actually gets inside, Cecil is in his house and explains to him that the recording from his fight with Omni Man has been released to the media. When Invincible asks him how he got into his house he tells him that he has the technology to teleport. In the meantime Derek, one of the kids who was abducted and almost turned into a living bomb causes trouble at school. Mark runs into Amber who immediately embraces him and they agree to talk later. Bulletproof is added to the Guardians of the Globe, and the Immortal is put in charge. Mark returns home to find his mom drunk on the floor and she tells him, \"Why did you have to fight him Mark? Why did you have to drive him away?\"</p>", "cv_id" => 125184, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185589-14.jpg", "issue_number" => 14.0, "name" => "Issue #14", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-14/4000-125184/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125187/", "cover_date" => "2004-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2017-09-08 19:05:39 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like most everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? Her decision is made up... her perfect mate is Invincible. No matter the cost... he must be hers. After her husband died in issue #7, Aquaria went through some bad times, but now that Mark has entered her life, everything is different, everything is perfect. Now Mark has to figure out how to let her know he's not interested... or legal.</em></p><p>Robot offers to help Monster Girl with her problem and she agrees that it would be nice to be the right age again. Deborah Grayson apologizes to Mark about the night before and he accepts her apology, because she was inebriated. Amber wonders why Mark needs a beeper because he keeps running out on her. Mark goes to the Pentagon, and Cecil tells them that he has to marry Aquarius' wife. Mark is shocked but Cecil tells him that he'll get him out of this. Mark is taken to Atlantis. Meanwhile Deborah meets with the publisher of Nolan's books and he says that Deborah will have an enormous check coming in a few weeks. Invincible is very worried when they say the wedding ceremony is today, and that he has to make love to a fish woman. He talks to Lethan the Queen's assistant and discovers that he really loves her so they devise a plan, and Lethan marries the queen, and Invincible narrowly escapes losing his virginity to a fish. Meanwhile Invincible discovers that his mom knows the wife of Superpatriot. Atom Eve and William have taken the next step in their relationship.</p>", "cv_id" => 125187, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185614-15.jpg", "issue_number" => 15.0, "name" => "Issue #15", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-15/4000-125187/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125240/", "cover_date" => "2004-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 18:19:32 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? EISNER AWARD NOMINEE FOR BEST NEW TITLE! The Immortal is back. Seemingly dead at the end of issue 7, he was brought back to life by The Maulers and has now decided to reclaim his status as leader of The Guardians of the Globe. This does not bode well for the current leader, Robot. And just how does all of this involve Invincible?</em></p><p>This issue begins in another reality. One where Invincible has decided to help his father take over earth for the Viltrumite empire. During this time we see Robot killed by Invincible, The Immortal killed by Omni-Man yet again. Angstrom Levy is taken to the real Invincible's reality (he is lead by himself from another dimension to the current reality we as the reader are aware of). Where an alien invasion is taking place, and Invincible, and the Guardians of the Globe are fighting them, They win against the aliens but a great deal of damage has occurred to Earth. Cecil agrees that the new Guardians of the Globe are not working out, and Robot is fired, and the Immortal is put in charge, yet he stays as a member of the team. Invincible and Atom Eve go to clean up the damage done by the Aliens. When cleaning up they see Titan throwing around rubble, they confront him and he informs them that he has changed his ways and Invincible buys it. Angstrom Levy brings the other Angstrom Levy to a warehouse full of Angstrom Levy's from other dimensions.</p>", "cv_id" => 125240, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185615-16.jpg", "issue_number" => 16.0, "name" => "Issue #16", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-16/4000-125240/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-125241/", "cover_date" => "2004-09-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 18:20:01 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? Old doors close as new ones open. Mark Grayson, AKA Invincible, has reached the end of his high school years. Watch as our hero dons that goofy-looking cap and gown and hope some big super-villain doesn't crash his graduation ceremony. Then again, what are the chances of THAT happening?</em></p><p>Invincible goes on a date with Amber, and they discuss their graduation. Angstrom Levy breaks the Mauler Twins out of jail, and they team up. Mark's school spends all their time watching movies, and Mark finds that his mother is drinking way too much. Invincible fights a monster with the Capes corporation who offer him a job, but he refuses. Mark graduates but when everyone is throwing their caps in the air his goes so high it lands in another country.</p>", "cv_id" => 125241, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185616-17.jpg", "issue_number" => 17.0, "name" => "Issue #17", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-17/4000-125241/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-126001/", "cover_date" => "2008-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2022-02-23 16:31:17 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>The Reanimen are back, but now they're fighting for the good guys?! And if that's the case, why are they facing off against Invincible? It all comes to a head here! Events are set in motion leading up to our big issue 50... coming next month!</em></p><p>Cecil tries to make contact with Mark but he doesn't reply because he is unconscious. Cecil walks into one of the labs and tells a scientist to get the new reanimen ready right now! Doc Seismic is gloating about his victory over almost all of their universe's superheroes, and he tells everyone that its Invincible's fault that he did this. He says that he was extremely happy in the underground he even thanked Mark for sending him to the depths. But when he took him back up to the surface and put him in jail he would never forget what he did. He yell out that he is doing this because of Invincible!</p><p>Invincible regains consciousness in a cacoon along with Atom-Eve. He is surprised that they lost the battle. Atom Eve asks Mark why Doc Seismic didn't kill them and he replies that he is quite old school, and thats probably not his style. Invincible tells Atom Eve that they can still get out of here, but when they do they have to let all of the other heroes out first. Just then Darkwing bursts through the wall with an army of reanimen yelling, \"ATTACK!\". He frees everybody from their captivity and they begin to fight the monsters. Darkwing is doing a great job, and Doc Seismic tells him that its to easy he says its not easy he just makes it look that way. Doc Seismic blasts Darkwing away and says that next time he will be victorious. Invincible lands beside him and tells him that its not the case while Invincible has him distracted Darkwing swoops in form the shadow verse and knocks Doc Seismic out cold.</p><p>Invincible hits Darkwing and yells murderer! Everyone looks surprised and Mark tries to explain that he killed many people in the past. Savage Dragon grabs Mark and says that he's a good guy. Robot even backs him up. Cecil teleports and tells Invincible to stand down, and leave.</p><p>Atom-Eve finds Mark in the snow, and they agree to talk about what happened between them earlier later. She asks Mark what got into him there and he tells her about the truth of Drakwing. He says he's made a grave mistake and he goes to find Cecil.</p><p>When he arrives he gives him shit about letting Darkwing free and says hes a murderer. Cecil brings up his encounter with Angstrom Levy and Invincible says that it was completely different. Just then the reanimen's creator walks in and says sorry I didn't know you were in a meeting. Cecil brings Mark into the white room and Mark asks why he brought him here. Cecil replies,\"For the element of surprise\" and Mark is attacked by many Reanimen.</p>", "cv_id" => 126001, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/8385858-5691411699-1.jpg.jpg", "issue_number" => 49.0, "name" => "Issue #49", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-49/4000-126001/", "store_date" => "2008-03-19"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-126528/", "cover_date" => "2006-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:34:07 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>The return of Doc Seismic but Mark's got his hands full doing detective work with William. Can they find Rick?</p><p>Rexplode isn't happy about the recent engagement of the Immortal, and DupliKate he complains about what he sees in her telling Bulletproof that all she wants to do is have sex. Bulletproof asks him isn't that why he went out with her, and he says yes. But if he was going to marry someone it would have to be someone like Eve. Just then the alarm goes off, and the Guardians of the Globe wisk off.</p><p>Invincible is flying around the city for his usual workout. He arrives back at his dorm room only to find a letter form the Dean about his absences. William tells Mark that he is worried about Rick and they should go look for him. Invincible agrees that they will later tonight.</p><p>The Guardians of the Globe are battling Doc Seismic he says that they cannot win. The downside is that there battling at the prison so many superheroes are escaping such as the Mauler Twins. The Immortal picks up Dupli-Kate telling her he won't have her hurt by these beasts she complains that he is embarrassing her and jumps off. Just then a new superhero jumps out of know where, and calls himself Shapesmith. The Guardians of the Globe have appeared to lost until One of the Mauler twins arrives and says he wants to turn himself in. The Guardians say really? But it is revealed to be Shapesmith who is offered a job, and turns Doc Seismic in. Robot is telling Monster Girl about the Rex Clone that he was put into, and asks her out she agrees.</p><p>Meanwhile Mark, and William begin there plan for William to be kidnapped by Reanimen, and Mark to come save him. Hours pass with nothing happening just then William is taken by a Reanimen into the sewers. Mark follows He complains about the sewers, and is surprised when he loses William but he than finds him a minute later. Out of know where he is attacked by 3 Reanimen, he takes the first two are easy for him, but when he rps the face mask off the other he discovers it is actually his friend Rick. H tries to tell Rick to snap out of it that this isn't him but he keeps on getting beaten.</p><p>D.A Sinclair brings William to his lair but William isn't worried he says that Mark will bust through a wall any minute now, but it doesn't happen fro a while and he gets very nervous.</p><p>Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 126528, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185657-36.jpg", "issue_number" => 36.0, "name" => "Issue #36", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-36/4000-126528/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-126819/", "cover_date" => "2007-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 05:25:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>In space alone...surrounded by Viltrumites Allen faces his fiercest fight yet!</p><p>Anissa throws Mark flying, than rushes back and grabs him she tells him that he has made a huge mistake, and slams him into the ground. She tells him that shes way stronger, fatser, and smarter than him she says that she will kill him if he even twitches. She asks if he has anything to say fror himself, and he says that she cracked his back, and it feels great now! She tells him that its his decision to secure the planet. She'll be back in a year of maybe even 5 months she does not want to be disappointed. Anissa flies into space, and a swat team arrives, and asks Mark if he need any help. He says he's fine and flies off.</p><p>In space Anissa arrives in the Viltrumite ship her captain asks how things went she says they could have gone better. She says that somehow some way they will be able to bring them to their side.</p><p>Mark meets back down with his mom, ans she asks what happened he is reluctant to discuss, and offers to fly her home she agrees, but tells him to pick up her car tonight. Mark arrives home to see Oliver, and meets April Oliver's tutor she tells him about his progress, and Oliver is very happy.</p><p>Meanwhile in space Allen is flying back to the Coalition of the Planets. He is thinking about his girlfriend, and about how much he loves her. He wishes he was able to marry her, but knows that will never happen. Just than he barely dodges a Viltrumite ship. He hopes the don't notice but Anissa comes flying out and Allen offers to talk it out. Anissa says no and Allen punches her. She asks when he got so strong, and tells him that Nolan is in the ship. Allen is punched but plays possum to enter the ship, and save Nolan.</p><p>Back at the University Mark, complains about the algebra to Mark. He says there is no use in him even doing it because hes failing anyway. He flies up in the sky, and thinks about whats coming in five months.</p><p>Deborah is on a date, and she says that what worries her is that her husband never loved her in the first place.</p><p>In space a prisoner asks Nolan why he looks so troubled. He says that each day he grows closer to execution, but the alien says its something else. Than he says, \"I THINK I MISS MY WIFE!\".</p>", "cv_id" => 126819, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/7/71975/2225231-6e4aa729_88a5_497e_be67_029aec491596.jpg", "issue_number" => 45.0, "name" => "Issue #45", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-45/4000-126819/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-126823/", "cover_date" => "2007-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:50:00 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>This issue is new reader friendly. It offers a greta story, plus a recap of the series, form start to finish.</p><p>Mark is on the moon talking to Cecil, he is on a mission to supervise the astronauts while thye are up there. Inside the space station two men say that they don't trust him because of what happened with Omni-Man. Suddenly another Astronaut form the Mars mission says that he saved her life, and does not care what they think. Cecil tells Marl he is needed back on earth, and he goes back.</p><p>There is a giant red monster attacking New York, so Invinicible beats him up. He demands to be made president of the united states, but is knocked out. Just than the Guardians of the Globe arrive, and Invincible heads back to space to help the Astronauts. </p><p>Back at the Pentagon Cecil tells Mark that the giant was actually an eight year old boy. That was sucked into another dimension when his grandma made an herbal remedy for their cat. He was enchanted, and became a king in that reality. Cecil tells Mark he did very good today, and Mark says thanks, and goes to a press conference. Mark is bombarded with questions about his dad, and he says that he does not owe an apology to the human race, for what his dad did, because he did everything in his power at the time to stop him.</p><p>Later at Marks dorm room Mark reads his father's books, and William says that reading them are ridiculous. Mark says thats its important, and tells him to be quiet. William says to calm down, and that he didn't really mean it. He asks Mark if he is okay and Mark says he doesn't know. He complains that he misses Amber, and that he feels like he is falling apart. William offers to ask Amber out, and says that if he hears him and Amber making that rubber bed shake than he will never think about her again. Mark says thats really wanted to hear sarcastically, and goes out. </p><p>Invincible fights Octoboss, and finishes him easy. But Octoboss let in a few good punches. When Mark arrives home his costume is ripped everywhere. He sees his mom, Deborah says to go see his brother because he misses him. Mark and Oliver play catch and Invincible accidentally throws it too high. Too Marks surprise Oliver starts flying and catches it. He says he wants too surprise mom.</p>", "cv_id" => 126823, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/17055/347576-17993-126823-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 42.0, "name" => "Issue #42", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-42/4000-126823/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-128555/", "cover_date" => "2004-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-15 13:41:11 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? Invincible is enlisted to accompany the first manned space flight to Mars. What secrets could the red planet hold? Why would someone anticipate a problem necessitating the inclusion of the most powerful superhero on the planet? Invincible is about to find out, and the answer will astound you!</em></p><p>Invincible escorts a shuttle to Mars. The astronauts encounter 'Martians' and another alien race called the \"Sequids\".</p>", "cv_id" => 128555, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185617-18.jpg", "issue_number" => 18.0, "name" => "Issue #18", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-18/4000-128555/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-128610/", "cover_date" => "2005-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 10:35:43 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is just like everyone else his age, except that his father is the most powerful superhero on the planet. And now he's begun to inherit his father's powers. It all sounds okay at first, but how do you follow in your father's footsteps when you know you will never live up to his standards? For nine years now (or however long it's been since issue #6 came out) readers have been wondering, \"What's up with that robot zombie from issue #6?\" Well, wonder no longer, because he's in this issue! Mark is on campus at his new college and something is amiss. What lurks behind...oh, wait: You already know!</em></p><p>Atom Eve decides to retire from the superhero business and use her powers to actually make a difference in the world. Amber gets mad at Mark when he mysteriously disappears to fight a Reaniman that is attacking the campus, she mistakenly thinks he ran off like a coward. If only she knew Mark is actually the brave superhero, Invincible. D. A. Sinclair formulates that his next Reaniman should be constructed from a...live subject!</p>", "cv_id" => 128610, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185628-20.jpg", "issue_number" => 20.0, "name" => "Issue #20", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-20/4000-128610/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-128945/", "cover_date" => "2005-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 10:44:10 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is the son of the most powerful superhero on the planet. Recently he's begun to inherit his father's powers, and in doing so, he has learned that everything he's been told is a lie. His father wasn't sent here to protect the planet, he was sent here to enslave it. The only thing that prevented him from succeeding was his own son. But he's still out there, and nobody knows when he will strike again. Return to Midnight City! Cast in the shadow of perpetual darkness, Midnight City lost its sole protector to Omni-Man, Invincible's father, as part of his plot to take over the world. Now many months have passed since the original Darkwing's death, and there's a new Darkwing in town. Invincible is curious to find out just who this guy is.</em></p><p>It all begins in Midnight City, a woman runs in terror throught the city. Running and screaming from a masked vigilante. Who is he and why is he terrorizing the the dark underworld city as the deceased \"Darkwing\"? Later at the United States Pentagon, the members of the Gaurdians of the Globe rest after their fight against \"Battle Beast\" and the crime lord \"Machine Mask\". Robot checks in on them to examine their condition, then consults with \"Donald\" about the teams members. Soon, \"Cencil\" alerts Invincible about the masked renegade roaming Midnight city and flies into action. Once entering the city, Invincible spots a cloaked figure huddling around two dead bodies. Mark starts to investigate the caped crusader, but is quickly interrupted by the man's lack of care for his investigation. The new Darkwing rushes pass Invincible and strikes him in the back.It is later that Darkwing vanishes into the shadows and suprise punches Invincible in the face. Mrak is able to grab hold of Darkwing's arm, but is dragged into a dark dimension where he cannot escape. Later the two heroes compromise and decide to leave the shadowdimension. Once they escape, Invinicble grabs the arms of Darkwing and flies off to the United States Pentagon. There, Darkwing is taken into arrest by Cecil and his agents. Soon after, \"Robot is seen getting repairs or upgrades by an unknown disformed man in a suit.</p>", "cv_id" => 128945, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185629-21.jpg", "issue_number" => 21.0, "name" => "Issue #21", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-21/4000-128945/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-129012/", "cover_date" => "2005-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 18:40:22 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark Grayson is the son of the most powerful superhero on the planet. Recently he's begun to inherit his father's powers, and in doing so, he has learned that everything he's been told is a lie. His father wasn't sent here to protect the planet, he was sent here to enslave it. The only thing that prevented him from succeeding was his own son. But he's still out there, and nobody knows when he will strike again. Mark and Amber's relationship is heating up now that they are in college and away from the prying eyes of parental supervision. Also in this issue, yet another person discovers Mark's secret identity. How does that Spider-Man guy do it? Oh, wait...never mind</em></p><p>Mark reveals to Amber, that he is Invincible and she is relieved to find out her boyfriend is not a drug dealer. Atom Eve is using her powers for good to help out man kind. Rick is kidnapped by D.A. Sinclair who plans on turning him into one of his Reanimen.</p>", "cv_id" => 129012, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185630-22.jpg", "issue_number" => 22.0, "name" => "Issue #22", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-22/4000-129012/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-129013/", "cover_date" => "2005-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 10:58:31 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Picking up right where the 50¢ issue #0 left off! Mark and Amber have come to a new understanding, things are different and now they're left wondering what's next for them. Meanwhile, something is happening in deep space. Luckily, Allen the Alien is on hand to deal with it, but will he be enough?</em></p><p>After Mark reveals himself to be the famous \"Invincible\", he and Amber have sex with one another. Later, in a galaxy far away, we find ,\"Allen the Alien\" roaming the universe and finally entering his home planet's atmosphere. He reports to the council on the what has occured on Earth. Allen states that a Viltrumite offspring resited in the invasion of the planet. That new led the council to believe that more viltumite offspring could be joined to their cause and destroy the vultrumite empire. Soon after, Allen returns to his girlfriend \"Telia\". They discuss why they cannot reproduce due to Allen's mating rules. They later make love, then go out for dinner. While in the middle of their meal, they are interrupted by viltrumite soilders that question him about \"Omni-man\" and \"Invincible\". Once Allen has told them what they wanted to know, they continue to tare off his arm, punch a hole in his stomach, and leave his broken body floating in sace. He is later visited in the medical center by \"Telia\" and the council member, it is later revealed that there is a spy in the council.</p>", "cv_id" => 129013, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185632-23.jpg", "issue_number" => 23.0, "name" => "Issue #23", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-23/4000-129013/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-129014/", "cover_date" => "2005-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-16 07:28:14 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Only once in his career has Invincible been beaten this badly. That time it was his father, Omni-Man, who had done the beating. Who could it be this time? This issue is a can't miss for any long-time fans of the book, and it's all leading up to the HUGE events in issue 25, coming next month.</em></p><p>After the Mauler Brothers completed their machine for Angstrom, they began their experiment. Unfortunately, Invincible crashed into the lab, ruining the procedure. This caused Angstrom to gather all the Mauler Brothers from their alternate universes to take care of Mark while Angstrom continues his experiments. While Angstrom rejected the Mauler Brothers attempt to kill Invincible, he lifted the helmet connected to the machine which caused and explosion that killed all of the alternate Mauler Brothers. Afterward, the Guardians of the Globe make the scene due to the explosion seen from the secret hideout. A surviving Mauler Brother find a deformed Angstrom, wanting revenge against Invincible for ruining his experiments and turning him into a monster. He then leaves the universe to plot for his revenge, leaving the surviving Mauler Brother stranded.</p>", "cv_id" => 129014, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185633-24.jpg", "issue_number" => 24.0, "name" => "Issue #24", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-24/4000-129014/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-129080/", "cover_date" => "2005-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 11:02:34 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>\"A Different World,\" Part One. The most climactic and earth-shattering story arc in Invincible history starts here! Events in issue 11 changed the status quo of this title forever and this arc will result in even more changes. Reality is not as it was, things are changed, and Mark comes face-to-face with his favorite imaginary hero, Science Dog -- but how is that even possible? Plus: A stand-alone Science Dog back-up story drawn by Invincible co-creator Cory Walker.</em></p><p>Invincible and Rex fight Octoboss and his Squidmen. Rex catches Dupli-Kate cheating on him with the Immortal. Invincible fights Science Dog who turns out to be an alien who took the form of the character. Invincible follows the alien back to their planet and meets....his Dad! The last part of the comic is filled with multiple origin stories by various artists. Origins include: Monster Girl, Immortal, Atom Eve, Rex Splode, Dupli-Kate, and Science Dog.</p>", "cv_id" => 129080, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185636-25.jpg", "issue_number" => 25.0, "name" => "Issue #25", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-25/4000-129080/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-497990/", "cover_date" => "2015-08-31", "date_last_updated" => "2019-09-13 05:47:48 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark and Eve try to enjoy a little down time as a chain of events is set into motion that will change the way you look at Mark Grayson forever.</em></p>", "cv_id" => 497990, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/4763057-122.jpg", "issue_number" => 122.0, "name" => "Issue #122", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-122/4000-497990/", "store_date" => "2015-08-19"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-129228/", "cover_date" => "2005-09-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-17 17:37:31 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Mark is in a world completely alien to him. How did he get there? What is happening around him? And who is trying to kill him? Answers to these questions and more as the most climactic and earth-shattering story arc in INVINCIBLE history continues!</em></p><p>Omni-Man tells Invincible what has happened since he left Earth. Invincible also learns he has a new half-brother!</p>", "cv_id" => 129228, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185639-26.jpg", "issue_number" => 26.0, "name" => "Issue #26", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-26/4000-129228/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130599/", "cover_date" => "2005-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-17 17:37:51 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>A massive gathering of heroes take on the supremely powerful Omnipotus, forcing him back through a portal. Out on the Mantis planet, Mark and his Father have a long talk that gets interrupted by three attacking Viltrumites. Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130599, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185640-27.jpg", "issue_number" => 27.0, "name" => "Issue #27", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-27/4000-130599/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130600/", "cover_date" => "2006-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 11:04:05 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Invincible struggles to protect his new Half-Brother and Step-Mom from a Viltrumite. Omni-Man steps in to help. Meanwhile the other Viltrumites massacre most of the Mantis race in order to lure out Omni-Man. Back on Earth, the Mauler twin makes a new clone of himself and Deborah gives up drinking. Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130600, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185641-28.jpg", "issue_number" => 28.0, "name" => "Issue #28", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-28/4000-130600/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130601/", "cover_date" => "2006-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-17 18:42:16 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Mighty battle between the Viltrumites and the father/son team. Back on Earth...Mauler clone poisons his Mauler brother and the clone cycle starts anew. Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130601, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185642-29.jpg", "issue_number" => 29.0, "name" => "Issue #29", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-29/4000-130601/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130602/", "cover_date" => "2006-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 11:05:03 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Invincible helps the Mantis race rebuild their world then returns home and surprises his Mom with his new half-brother. Robot shows up at the Mauler Twins' lab. Next, Mark catches up with the other people in his life, most of whom are more than a little upset with his surprising two month disappearance. Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130602, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185646-30.jpg", "issue_number" => 30.0, "name" => "Issue #30", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-30/4000-130602/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130605/", "cover_date" => "2006-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 11:05:42 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>The Guardians of the Globe fight Mastermind, a mind controlling menace. Deborah bonds with Mark's new half-brother and decides to adopt him. Mark and Amber go to Africa to visit Atom Eve.</p><p>Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130605, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185647-31.jpg", "issue_number" => 31.0, "name" => "Issue #31", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-31/4000-130605/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130606/", "cover_date" => "2006-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 09:51:10 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Mark and Atom Eve catch up. Amber enjoys the Africa trip but is slightly left out, with the other two being superheros. Angstrom Levy threatens Invincible's Mom and Half-brother.</p><p>Shapesmith makes his first costumed debut in this issue and single-handedly battles the Lizard League.</p>", "cv_id" => 130606, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185648-32.jpg", "issue_number" => 32.0, "name" => "Issue #32", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-32/4000-130606/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130607/", "cover_date" => "2006-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 09:57:45 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Invincible fights Angstrom Levy in order to save his family...but Angstrom doesn't fight fair! He teleports Invincible to dimension after dimension, in order to weaken Invincible enough so that he Angstrom can beat him. Int the end they get into a massive fist fight while teleporting through different dimensions. Invincible, in a blind rage, hammers on Angstrom for beating his Mother....and uses too much force!</p><p>This issue ties in with Marvel Team-Up (2006) #14.</p>", "cv_id" => 130607, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185649-33.jpg", "issue_number" => 33.0, "name" => "Issue #33", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-33/4000-130607/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130609/", "cover_date" => "2006-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-18 10:00:27 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>Mark tries to deal with murdering Angstrom. A future Guardians of the Globe visit Mark and talk with him, then he is sent back to his home dimension. His Mom and Half-brother turn out ok. Meanwhile Robot breaks his end of the bargain with the Mauler Twins.</p><p>Features a Capes backup story.</p>", "cv_id" => 130609, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2185650-34.jpg", "issue_number" => 34.0, "name" => "Issue #34", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-34/4000-130609/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-130610/", "cover_date" => "2007-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-23 15:51:18 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Allen the Alien has returned to Earth, seeking more information from Invincible that he can use against the Viltrumite Empire. Unfortunately, The Immortal is giving Allen a less-than-warm welcome.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 130610, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/6539/394375-17993-130610-1-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 43.0, "name" => "Issue #43", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-43/4000-130610/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-131455/", "cover_date" => "2008-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2016-10-24 01:36:22 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>It’s all been building to this. After five long years, the best superhero comic book in the universe has reached its monumental FIFTIETH ISSUE! Invincible and Cecil Stedman face off and after this issue, nothing will ever be the same. Also in this issue, Science Dog returns in an all-new back-up story... and the ORIGIN OF CECIL STEDMAN!</p>", "cv_id" => 131455, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3664/419257-x.jpg", "issue_number" => 50.0, "name" => "Issue #50", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-50/4000-131455/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-134119/", "cover_date" => "2008-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 05:32:03 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<em>Overview:<br /></em><br /><p> New costume! New beginning! New home! New Partner! Everything is all-new starting with this issue. Featuring an all-new cover by comic book super-star JIM LEE! If you’ve ever thought about reading INVINCIBLE this is the jumping-on point you’ve been waiting for. The next fifty issues start here!</p>", "cv_id" => 134119, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/463888-invincible51_cover.jpg", "issue_number" => 51.0, "name" => "Issue #51", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-51/4000-134119/", "store_date" => "2008-07-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-138424/", "cover_date" => "2008-09-30", "date_last_updated" => "2023-03-06 16:23:45 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>This partnership is not off to a good start! It’s brother versus brother and the outcome of this all out brawl will amaze you. Who will be left standing? The bold new direction of INVINCIBLE continues here!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 138424, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/537644-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 52.0, "name" => "Mark! Get Down Here, Now!", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-52-mark-get-down-here-now/4000-138424/", "store_date" => "2008-09-10"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-139696/", "cover_date" => "2008-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2023-03-06 16:24:01 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>Overview:<br /><br /></i> <p> A few issues back, Titan tricked Invincible into helping him take over Machine Head’s arm of the criminal organization knows as THE ORDER – and Invincible is not too happy about being tricked.</p>", "cv_id" => 139696, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/566087-invincible53_cover.jpg", "issue_number" => 53.0, "name" => "Wow, Just...Wow", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-53-wow-justwow/4000-139696/", "store_date" => "2008-10-01"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-140811/", "cover_date" => "2008-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-25 03:27:59 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>FIGHTMASTER AND DROP KICK RETURN!</i></p><p><i>They’re back from the future to alter the past – can Invincible stop them – or will he be lost in the time stream forever? Also in this issue: Kid Omni-Man saves the day.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 140811, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/592261-inv.jpg", "issue_number" => 54.0, "name" => "Issue #54", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-54/4000-140811/", "store_date" => "2008-10-22"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-142745/", "cover_date" => "2008-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-26 05:16:44 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p> <i>Omni-Man has been awaiting execution in a Viltrumite Prison for months, but Allen the Alien has different plans for Invincible’s father. The stage is set for the final confrontation with the Viltrumites –- and it all starts here!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 142745, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/618356-invincible55_cover.jpg", "issue_number" => 55.0, "name" => "Lock Down, But Not Out", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-55-lock-down-but-not-out/4000-142745/", "store_date" => "2008-11-19"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-145547/", "cover_date" => "2008-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-27 02:51:55 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p> <em>When someone very close to Invincible is hurt – the gloves come off! Is Mark Grayson’s murderous Viltrumite heritage finally coming to the forefront? Find out in this special stand-alone issue that answers the question once and for all: can Invincible be driven to MURDER?</em></p>", "cv_id" => 145547, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/638220-invincible56_cover.jpg", "issue_number" => 56.0, "name" => "Issue #56", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-56/4000-145547/", "store_date" => "2008-12-10"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-148141/", "cover_date" => "2008-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-19 06:13:25 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>At the secret base of the former \"Teen Team\", Robot inspects the remains of the device that Invincible brought. Robot decided that the device was meant to spy on Invincible and his family. After hearing the news, Invincible flies off to the United States Pentagon. Soon, after breaking their defenses, Invincible stops after Cecil makes his appearance. Cecil claims he had nothing to do with the device that was captured by Invincible and his teammates. Eventually, Invincible calms down and is asked for a favor by Cecil and his comrade. Somewhere else, \"The Elder\" trains the Astounding Wolf-Man for the battles yet to come. Soon after, Gary transforms into his wolf-like state and jumps off into the forest. Back at the Pentagon, Invincible is asked to take out the Astounding Wolf-Man. Mark refuses at irst, but when the giant escapes along side the Wolf-Man on his back, it would be taking out to birds with one stone. In the forest, Gary battles the giant whose wrecking down the entire forest in a matter of seconds. In the midst of the battle, Invincible flies in and knocks the giant right in the back of his head and catches Gary. When the giant started to rise from the ground, Mark knocked him off of his feet and puts him down for good. Soon, the response team arrives and captures the giant creature, it is later revealed that the giant was just a kid who was pulled into another dimension and genetically altered. Eventually, Invincible stated that he still had to turn over Gary to Cecil at the Pentagon. After hearing that, Gary leaps off into the air only to be punched back to the ground by Invincible. Gary tries to explain that he did not kill his wife and that he was innocent. Gary then returned back into his human for to prove his point about him being not guilty. Soon after, they return to the Pentagon to tell Cecil what truly happened that night that Gary's wife was killed. Refusing to hear the argument, Cecil calls the guards and commands them to take out both Invincible and Astounding Wolf-Man. </p>", "cv_id" => 148141, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/11863/653039-invincible57_cover_1_.jpg", "issue_number" => 57.0, "name" => "Invincible vs. The Astounding Wolf-Man, Part 1", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-57-invincible-vs-the-astounding-wolf-ma/4000-148141/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-150046/", "cover_date" => "2009-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-27 04:08:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Invincible and Atom Eve are finally together. Young love... how interesting.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 150046, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/1/15455/676644-inv.jpg", "issue_number" => 58.0, "name" => "Young Love...", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-58-young-love/4000-150046/", "store_date" => "2009-01-14"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-152425/", "cover_date" => "2009-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-27 03:12:40 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-style:italic;\">Meet PowerPlex! He's out to rid the world once and for all of the menace known as Invincible!</span>", "cv_id" => 152425, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/31567/714219-invincible59.jpg", "issue_number" => 59.0, "name" => "Meet Powerplex", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-59-meet-powerplex/4000-152425/", "store_date" => "2009-02-18"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-153703/", "cover_date" => "2009-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 06:20:06 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE CROSSOVER EVENT OF THE DECADE! Invincible is drawn into a company-wide crossover event done in ONE oversized issue! SPAWN! SAVAGE DRAGON! YOUNGBLOOD! SHADOWHAWK! CYBERFORCE! PITT! ULTRA! and many, many more all here for one issue – don't miss it!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 153703, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/740287-60.jpg", "issue_number" => 60.0, "name" => "The Invincible War", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-60-the-invincible-war/4000-153703/", "store_date" => "2009-03-18"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-155799/", "cover_date" => "2009-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 06:12:57 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>INVINCIBLE WAR: AFTERMATH! The planet is in ruins. Everything has changed, the world's superheroes are in the hospital or dead. Invincible is left to rebuild -- but now he must face his most deadly and powerful adversary yet. Who... or what is CONQUEST?</i>", "cv_id" => 155799, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3853/774216-invincible61.jpg", "issue_number" => 61.0, "name" => "Conquest Part One", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-61-conquest-part-one/4000-155799/", "store_date" => "2009-04-22"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-157824/", "cover_date" => "2009-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 06:16:38 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>After coming to Earth in the last issue, Conquest enters the fight with Invinciblbe. Their battle takes place from the ruined city streets and skies to the very cold space. Kid Omni-Man later joins the fight after watching them on the television. Unfortunetly, Mark pushes him out of the battle, he said it was too dangerous for him.<br /></i>", "cv_id" => 157824, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/3853/807232-invincible61.jpg", "issue_number" => 62.0, "name" => "Conquest Part Two", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-62-conquest-part-two/4000-157824/", "store_date" => "2009-05-20"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-160437/", "cover_date" => "2009-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 06:19:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>INVINCIBLE WAR: AFTERMATH!<br /><br />CONQUEST IS HERE! The fate of the entire planet rests on Invincible's shoulders... and those shoulders are about to break. </i><br />", "cv_id" => 160437, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/841432-63.jpg", "issue_number" => 63.0, "name" => "Conquest Part Three", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-63-conquest-part-three/4000-160437/", "store_date" => "2009-06-17"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-164880/", "cover_date" => "2009-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 17:22:59 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>The battle with CONQUEST concludes... and there is a casualty. </i>", "cv_id" => 164880, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/887927-64.jpg", "issue_number" => 64.0, "name" => "Conquest: Conclusion", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-64-conquest-conclusion/4000-164880/", "store_date" => "2009-07-22"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-172353/", "cover_date" => "2009-09-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 11:05:52 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Artist CORY WALKER returns to the series he co-created! After escaping from a Viltrumite Prison, Nolan Grayson and Allen the Alien must use what they've learned to gather the powers of the universe and unite them against the Viltumites. It all starts here, folks: The Viltrumite War looms large on the horizon!</em></p>", "cv_id" => 172353, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/964904-66.jpg", "issue_number" => 66.0, "name" => "Preparations For War! Part 1", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-66-preparations-for-war-part-1/4000-172353/", "store_date" => "2009-09-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-177659/", "cover_date" => "2009-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-10-02 19:34:52 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Artist CORY WALKER returns to the series he co-created! After escaping from a Viltrumite Prison, Nolan Grayson and Allen the Alien must use what they've learned to gather the powers of the universe and unite them against the Viltumites. It all starts here, folks! The Viltrumite War looms large on the horizon!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 177659, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/999388-67.jpg", "issue_number" => 67.0, "name" => "Preparations For War! Part 2; Image United Prelude, Part 3", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-67-preparations-for-war-part-2-image-un/4000-177659/", "store_date" => "2009-10-21"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-183787/", "cover_date" => "2009-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 11:16:52 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>We return to Earth after the brief space interlude involving Nolan and Allen the Alien... but is it the Earth we knew?! What changes have taken place? What has transpired in the time we were away? Who is DINOSAURUS?! This issue is a can't-miss for long-time fans of Invincible and an excellent jumping-on point for people who have yet to dip their toes in the INVINCIBLE waters.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 183787, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/9116/1031201-68.jpg", "issue_number" => 68.0, "name" => "Issue #68", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-68/4000-183787/", "store_date" => "2009-11-18"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-189593/", "cover_date" => "2009-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 11:21:06 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i>EVERYTHING IS DIFFERENT NOW! <br />Who is Universa?! Why did she come to this planet in search of the one called Invincible? What does it have to do with the impending Viltrumite Invasion?! And why did she decide to come NOW, on the eve of an attack from the SEQUIDS?! The answers to all these questions and even more questions piled on top of them – in this issue of Invincible.</i>  <br /> <b><br />SPOILERS</b><br /> <br />The story begins with a new character Universa making her way to Earth. Kirkman describes her as a warrior queen who has traveled countless miles to the planet earth, and will not stop until she gets what she has come for as her planet is in grave danger. Next, we see Rus Livingston fully possessed by Sequids reeking havoc. The Sequid invasion has begun.<br /> Mark &amp; Eve are discussing what happened last issue (It’s a major spoiler, I won’t spoil it for people just beginning the series) just then Eve receives a call that they are needed. When Mark, and Eve arrive on the scene Universa is attacking a Nucear power plant. She has a special kind of staff that wields the power of two light spectrums and turns them into one blast thus creating an unstoppable power. Invincible commences the battle with her, and later is partly defeated evidently leaving Eve to help fight Universa while he recovers. Unfortunately Eve is still having trouble with her powers.<br /> The Guardians of the Globe led by Brit go to stop the Sequid threat. They create a type of barrier, and appear to have everything handled. Off panel we return to Invincible’s battle with Universa. Mark steals her staff, only to be electrocuted by its fail safe Invincible appears to be defeated until Eve now powerless (per-say) leaves her unconscious with a left hook. Seconds later Cecil arrives and asks for Mark’s help against the Sequid Invasion. Mark assumes that they have the situation handled. The issue ends with a splash page in which Rus Livingston has defeated the Guardian of the Globe.", "cv_id" => 189593, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/38919/1071696-invincible_69.jpg", "issue_number" => 69.0, "name" => "Issue #69", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-69/4000-189593/", "store_date" => "2009-12-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-198005/", "cover_date" => "2010-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 11:22:38 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i> Invincible finds himself faced against the combined might of the Sequid legions! Is he willing to do what must be done in order to save the world -- and will this event push him over the edge or bring him back from it?</i>", "cv_id" => 198005, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/36359/1136724-invincible70_1.jpg", "issue_number" => 70.0, "name" => "OVERWHELMED!", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-70-overwhelmed/4000-198005/", "store_date" => "2010-02-17"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-211115/", "cover_date" => "2010-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-30 04:57:08 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>THE VILTRUMITE WAR BEGINS! <br />The entire series has been leading up to this! The pieces are in place, the time to strike is now! It's all out war as the Coalition of Planets finally make its move against the Viltrum Empire--with Invincible stuck in the middle. Things will never be the same after this--and this is INVINCIBLE, so you know we mean it.</p>", "cv_id" => 211115, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/3/38919/1211311-invincible_71.jpg", "issue_number" => 71.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 1", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-71-the-viltrumite-war-part-1/4000-211115/", "store_date" => "2010-04-28"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-217479/", "cover_date" => "2010-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 16:45:30 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<i> THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES! <br />You all knew it was coming, so might  as well get it out of the way early: CONQUEST vs. INVINCIBLE - the  rematch!  This time Invincible won’t have Atom Eve to help him, and  Conquest won’t make the mistake of underestimating him.  Can a  galaxy-spanning all-out war contain this fight?  This issue is not to be  missed!  </i>", "cv_id" => 217479, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/0/6063/1251332-invincible.jpg", "issue_number" => 72.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 2", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-72-the-viltrumite-war-part-2/4000-217479/", "store_date" => "2010-06-03"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-222076/", "cover_date" => "2010-06-30", "date_last_updated" => "2015-10-02 19:34:15 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES!<br />Invincible is stranded on an alien planet, clinging to life, left battered and broken from his battle with Conquest. Nolan and Oliver stay behind to nurse him back to health, but meanwhile, out in space, the war rages on.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 222076, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/56299/1283796-invincible_issue_73.jpg", "issue_number" => 73.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 3", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-73-the-viltrumite-war-part-3/4000-222076/", "store_date" => "2010-06-30"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-231788/", "cover_date" => "2010-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 16:55:03 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<em>VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES! The traitor is revealed as the Viltrumite Empire's Grand Regent Thragg launches a full-scale assault on the Coalition of Planets home base on Talescria. It appears that all is lost, but the Coalition isn't going to go down without a fight.</em>", "cv_id" => 231788, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/56299/1356925-invincible_issue_74.jpg", "issue_number" => 74.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 4", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-74-the-viltrumite-war-part-4/4000-231788/", "store_date" => "2010-08-25"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-241001/", "cover_date" => "2010-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-10-02 19:34:03 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES!</i></p><p><i>Invincible and the Coalition of Planets bring the war to Planet Viltrum! All bets are off as the Coalition forces try to fight their way into the Viltrumite Empire’s stronghold. Lives are lost, and the war reaches a turning point. This issue features as special, over-sized main story and an extra special Science Dog back-up story by ROBERT KIRKMAN and CORY WALKER.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 241001, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/58664/1489991-prv6860_cov.jpg", "issue_number" => 75.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 5", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-75-the-viltrumite-war-part-5/4000-241001/", "store_date" => "2010-11-03"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-250786/", "cover_date" => "2010-12-22", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 17:00:23 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES!</i></p><p><i>It’s all been leading up to this: Invincible vs. Thragg, one-on-one! It’s the fight to end all fights, and the fate of the entire universe hangs in the balance. Whatever you do, don’t miss this issue!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 250786, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/58664/1579478-invincible76_cover.jpg", "issue_number" => 76.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 6", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-76-the-viltrumite-war-part-6/4000-250786/", "store_date" => nil})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-260308/", "cover_date" => "2011-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 17:04:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES! THE FINAL STAND! It’s all come to this: The fate of all life on Earth is at stake. If Invincible loses... Wait, Invincible can’t lose... Can he?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 260308, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/5/58664/1651880-invincible.77.01.jpg", "issue_number" => 77.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 7", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-77-the-viltrumite-war-part-7/4000-260308/", "store_date" => "2011-02-02"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-266629/", "cover_date" => "2011-03-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-28 17:09:45 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>THE VILTRUMITE WAR CONTINUES!</i></p><p><i>The dust is settling, the war is over... but nothing will ever be the same. Mark and Eve, Nolan and Debbie are reunited, but the Viltrumites have... well... you’ll just have to read the book to find out...</i></p>", "cv_id" => 266629, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/87073/1736070-invincible78.jpg", "issue_number" => 78.0, "name" => "The Viltrumite War: Part 8", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-78-the-viltrumite-war-part-8/4000-266629/", "store_date" => "2011-03-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-268788/", "cover_date" => "2011-04-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-29 13:54:04 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>In the aftermath of the VILTRUMITE WAR, Invincible returns home to find things on Earth are very different.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 268788, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/8/87073/1780872-invincible79.jpg", "issue_number" => 79.0, "name" => "Issue #79", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-79/4000-268788/", "store_date" => "2011-04-20"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-273273/", "cover_date" => "2011-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2018-04-09 09:06:04 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>DINOSAURUS returns! Hellbent on righting what he sees as wrong in the world he comes face-to-face with Invincible and the result is devastating.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 273273, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2669997-80.jpg", "issue_number" => 80.0, "name" => "Issue #80", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-80/4000-273273/", "store_date" => "2011-06-15"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-281928/", "cover_date" => "2011-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-29 14:09:25 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><em>Invincible continues making up for lost time while he was out in space fighting The Viltrumite War. His efforts bring him face-to-face with PowerPlex, who still blames Invincible for the death of his wife and son. The thing is, these days Invincible has plenty to be angry about as well, so things are about to get intense!</em></p>", "cv_id" => 281928, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/1966724-81.jpg", "issue_number" => 81.0, "name" => "Issue #81", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-81/4000-281928/", "store_date" => "2011-07-27"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-290678/", "cover_date" => "2011-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-29 14:19:55 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Face-to-face with Universa. She came from a distant planet, wielding unimaginable power, seeking to drain our planet dry of all energy. Invincible was able to stop her. But how long can she be contained... and what can be done with her?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 290678, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/10/101110/1988011-inv_82_001.jpg", "issue_number" => 82.0, "name" => "Issue #82", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-82/4000-290678/", "store_date" => "2011-08-31"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-294297/", "cover_date" => "2011-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-29 14:24:11 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Tether Tyrant and Magmaniac have long stood on the sidelines of the villain community - until now! Invincible has more than enough to deal with now that his life is in ruins dealing with the aftermath of... oh, that would be telling.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 294297, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/10/101110/2030706-inv_83_001.jpg", "issue_number" => 83.0, "name" => "Issue #83", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-83/4000-294297/", "store_date" => "2011-10-05"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-301056/", "cover_date" => "2011-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-29 14:26:46 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>After all he's done, everything he's lived through... how does Invincible pick up the pieces and continue on as if nothing has changed? The answer is... he can't.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 301056, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/10/101110/2066429-inv_84_001.jpg", "issue_number" => 84.0, "name" => "Issue #84", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-84/4000-301056/", "store_date" => "2011-11-02"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-303553/", "cover_date" => "2011-11-30", "date_last_updated" => "2017-06-17 11:14:39 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>CORY WALKER RETURNS TO INVINCIBLE! In this special two-issue story-arc: Invincible's mother and father return to the planet Talescria in the aftermath of The Viltrumite War! Omni-Man and Young Omni-Man reunite and fight space crime together! All the while, a new threat is emerging... one that could bring an end to all life on Earth!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 303553, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2161741-85.jpg", "issue_number" => 85.0, "name" => "Issue #85", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-85/4000-303553/", "store_date" => "2011-11-23"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-307878/", "cover_date" => "2011-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-06-30 05:02:15 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>CORY WALKER RETURNS TO INVINCIBLE! Allen thinks he's doing what's right - what must be done, but could he be wrong? Nolan and Young Omni-Man must do whatever it takes to prevent him from completing his mission, could this be the end of Allen The Alien?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 307878, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/7/73936/2135117-invincible_086__2011__pagecover.jpg", "issue_number" => 86.0, "name" => "Issue #86", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-86/4000-307878/", "store_date" => "2011-12-21"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-310923/", "cover_date" => "2012-01-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 03:19:59 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>RYAN OTTLEY RETURNS TO INVINCIBLE!</i></p><p><i>It came from outer space--and Invincible was completely unprepared. Get ready for another classic beat down in the grand Invincible fashion--but what does this have to do with The Viltrumites?</i></p><p>Invincible remains on the run with Dinosaurus, but interacts with past friends. Meanwhile, Allen and Oliver arrive at Earth ready to enact their plan.</p>", "cv_id" => 310923, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3446370-87.jpg", "issue_number" => 87.0, "name" => "Issue #87", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-87/4000-310923/", "store_date" => "2012-01-11"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-313909/", "cover_date" => "2012-02-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 03:23:23 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Invincible versus Young Omni-Man! WHAT?!!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 313909, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3446371-88.jpg", "issue_number" => 88.0, "name" => "Issue #88", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-88/4000-313909/", "store_date" => "2012-02-01"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-317973/", "cover_date" => "2012-02-29", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 03:30:46 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p>EVERYTHING IS DIFFERENT NOW!</p><p><i>There's someone new in the Invincible costume, but why - and for how long? Answers to all these questions and more in this monumental status-quo-altering issue!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 317973, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3446372-89.jpg", "issue_number" => 89.0, "name" => "Issue #89", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-89/4000-317973/", "store_date" => "2012-02-29"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-335054/", "cover_date" => "2012-05-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 03:43:02 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>The new Invincible will not back down, will not give in, and he is not going to play nice. What happens when Mark Grayson isn't happy with his replacement? All this and... What exactly happened between Robot and Monster Girl in the Flaxan Dimension?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 335054, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3446374-91.jpg", "issue_number" => 91.0, "name" => "Issue #91", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-91/4000-335054/", "store_date" => "2012-05-09"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-340275/", "cover_date" => "2012-06-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 04:47:17 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>CORY WALKER RETURNS TO INVINCIBLE… AGAIN!</i></p><p><i>What has been going on with Monster Girl and Robot? What happened to them while they were in the Flaxan dimension? All answers will be revealed – starting now!</i></p><p><i>Meanwhile, trouble is brewing in the present and the New Invincible is already in over his head! All this – and where is Mark Grayson?!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 340275, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/3446375-92.jpg", "issue_number" => 92.0, "name" => "Issue #92", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-92/4000-340275/", "store_date" => "2012-06-13"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-344118/", "cover_date" => "2012-07-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 04:21:56 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>More secrets about Robot's and Monster Girl's time spent in the Flaxan Dimension are revealed. Meanwhile, in the present - things go to hell, and the new Invincible has to prove if he's worthy of the mantle in the face of... INVASION.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 344118, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/7/71975/2445147-prev_img.jpg", "issue_number" => 93.0, "name" => "Issue #93", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-93/4000-344118/", "store_date" => "2012-07-04"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-352728/", "cover_date" => "2012-08-01", "date_last_updated" => "2017-06-17 11:42:02 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>The new Invincible faces defeat at the hands of the Flaxan Army! The Guardians of the Globe have fallen! What is Monster Girl and Robot's part in all this? How are they responsible? More of their past in the Flaxan dimension is revealed. And where is Mark Grayson during all this?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 352728, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/7/71975/2532027-prev_img.jpg", "issue_number" => 94.0, "name" => "Issue #94", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-94/4000-352728/", "store_date" => "2012-08-22"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-358865/", "cover_date" => "2012-09-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 04:26:12 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>In the Flaxan dimension, the events that placed Robot and Monster Girl at odds finally unfold as the sad truth comes to light. On Earth--everyone is getting their butts kicked by the Flaxans--will the new Invincible be able to turn the tide? And where is Mark Grayson during all this?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 358865, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2611363-95.jpg", "issue_number" => 95.0, "name" => "Issue #95", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-95/4000-358865/", "store_date" => "2012-09-26"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-363095/", "cover_date" => "2012-10-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-01 04:52:51 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>The Flaxan invasion comes to a horrible, violent end. Robot and Monster Girl will never be the same again as their secrets are revealed. The new Invincible has gotten a taste for what his new role will require. Meanwhile, back at home... Mark Grayson is growing stronger.</i></p>", "cv_id" => 363095, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/67663/2676139-96.jpg", "issue_number" => 96.0, "name" => "Issue #96", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-96/4000-363095/", "store_date" => "2012-10-24"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-367681/", "cover_date" => "2012-11-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 15:39:49 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>Finally, at long last: the origin of Zandale Randolph, otherwise known as Invincible. Also in this issue, an update on Mark Grayson, as the stage is set for the MONUMENTAL 100TH ISSUE! Do not miss out!</i></p>", "cv_id" => 367681, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/66303/2699931-prv14199_cov.jpeg", "issue_number" => 97.0, "name" => "Issue #97", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-97/4000-367681/", "store_date" => "2012-11-14"})
comic_14.issues.create!({"currency" => usd, "aliases" => nil, "api_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/issue/4000-371155/", "cover_date" => "2012-12-01", "date_last_updated" => "2015-07-05 15:15:35 UTC", "deck" => nil, "description" => "<p><i>\"THE DEATH OF EVERYONE,\" Part One</i></p><p><i>The countdown to issue #100 begins here - with the story that will change EVERYTHING for Invincible! Mark's powers have finally returned, just in time for every life on Earth to rest in his hands. But what will happen when everyone learns that what is happening... is Mark's fault?</i></p>", "cv_id" => 371155, "image" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/6/66303/2734630-invincible98_cover.jpeg", "issue_number" => 98.0, "name" => "The Death of Everyone, Part One", "site_detail_url" => "https://comicvine.gamespot.com/invincible-98-the-death-of-everyone-part-one/4000-371155/", "store_date" => "2012-12-05"})
